1
00:00:33,798 --> 00:00:37,168
(Yongheung Elementary School Autumn Field Day)

2
00:00:38,438 --> 00:00:40,238
(A trump card with a twist)

3
00:00:40,938 --> 00:00:42,937
(Together with Chef Ahn Sung Jae)

4
00:00:42,938 --> 00:00:43,938
Run!

5
00:00:44,408 --> 00:00:48,248
(A gift-like day)

6
00:00:49,878 --> 00:00:52,818
(Now, it's acting.)

7
00:00:52,948 --> 00:00:54,047
- Yes!
- Yes!

8
00:00:54,048 --> 00:00:57,558
(The teachers' passionate effort)

9
00:00:58,958 --> 00:01:02,058
(Dance routine by Potato Teacher)

10
00:01:02,958 --> 00:01:07,468
(One day, a question from Kyung Mo)

11
00:01:07,768 --> 00:01:08,797
(How long are we doing this?)

12
00:01:08,798 --> 00:01:13,198
(Kyung Mo's question)

13
00:01:14,138 --> 00:01:16,868
(Kids are unpredictable.)

14
00:01:17,278 --> 00:01:18,978
With courage

15
00:01:20,878 --> 00:01:25,178
(Will the teachers' sincerity reach the students?)

16
00:01:27,748 --> 00:01:31,258
(Mungyeong's fine morning)

17
00:01:32,658 --> 00:01:34,757
Today's weather is perfect for a run.

18
00:01:34,758 --> 00:01:35,788
Right?

19
00:01:37,428 --> 00:01:39,157
It's about 4°C higher than yesterday.

20
00:01:39,158 --> 00:01:40,327
- Is that so?
- It's 4°C higher.

21
00:01:40,328 --> 00:01:41,328
(North Pole and Potato are out on a morning jog.)

22
00:01:42,168 --> 00:01:44,298
There are many mountains here. We're surrounded by them.

23
00:01:45,138 --> 00:01:47,308
They look redder than yesterday.

24
00:01:47,368 --> 00:01:49,137
Right? The colors change every day.

25
00:01:49,138 --> 00:01:50,138
Yes.

26
00:01:50,139 --> 00:01:52,238
(The green mountains...)

27
00:01:53,648 --> 00:01:57,118
(have turned colorful.)

28
00:01:58,448 --> 00:02:01,148
(The green grass covering Yongheung Elementary School...)

29
00:02:02,848 --> 00:02:06,588
(has also turned autumnal.)

30
00:02:07,558 --> 00:02:10,227
Since coming here, I've been living a disciplined life.

31
00:02:10,228 --> 00:02:11,228
Right?

32
00:02:11,229 --> 00:02:12,598
- I feel healthier.
- Same here.

33
00:02:13,028 --> 00:02:14,597
- Tired, but healthier.
- Exactly.

34
00:02:14,598 --> 00:02:16,728
(Eating, running, teaching, and sleeping)

35
00:02:18,038 --> 00:02:19,568
This place is amazing.

36
00:02:19,738 --> 00:02:20,967
- Right?
- Look at the landscape.

37
00:02:20,968 --> 00:02:22,837
- This is wild.
- Unbelievable.

38
00:02:22,838 --> 00:02:24,778
(Entered a must-see landscape)

39
00:02:25,938 --> 00:02:26,938
There are birds.

40
00:02:26,939 --> 00:02:29,178
(There are even birds.)

41
00:02:30,278 --> 00:02:31,718
The birds will soon fly away.

42
00:02:32,678 --> 00:02:33,788
They're getting ready.

43
00:02:34,788 --> 00:02:36,488
- Action.
- Fly away.

44
00:02:37,088 --> 00:02:38,088
(Impressed)

45
00:02:38,818 --> 00:02:40,358
Goodness.

46
00:02:41,088 --> 00:02:42,128
How pretty.

47
00:02:42,388 --> 00:02:43,758
They're theater actors.

48
00:02:44,328 --> 00:02:45,827
They flew away when I said "action."

49
00:02:45,828 --> 00:02:47,228
How beautiful.

50
00:02:49,068 --> 00:02:50,368
My body is starting to feel light.

51
00:02:50,538 --> 00:02:52,067
- What?
- My body is starting to feel light.

52
00:02:52,068 --> 00:02:53,138
Me too.

53
00:02:55,068 --> 00:02:56,537
We need to go get kimchi.

54
00:02:56,538 --> 00:02:58,538
Right. That's the way to the place.

55
00:02:59,138 --> 00:03:00,347
We need to buy cabbage kimchi.

56
00:03:00,348 --> 00:03:02,578
(When the all-purpose truck came in Episode 3)

57
00:03:03,308 --> 00:03:05,317
(Failed to buy kimchi)

58
00:03:05,318 --> 00:03:06,417
Would you like some aged kimchi?

59
00:03:06,418 --> 00:03:08,018
- Yes.
- We'll buy some from you.

60
00:03:08,148 --> 00:03:10,287
- No, just take some.
- No way.

61
00:03:10,288 --> 00:03:12,688
(Invited by a generous elderly neighbor)

62
00:03:14,058 --> 00:03:15,058
Is this the place?

63
00:03:15,059 --> 00:03:16,227
(And so, they visit the warm-hearted old lady.)

64
00:03:16,228 --> 00:03:17,298
Ma'am.

65
00:03:17,798 --> 00:03:18,898
Yes?

66
00:03:19,458 --> 00:03:21,297
- Hi, ma'am.
- Hi.

67
00:03:21,298 --> 00:03:23,768
- Welcome. Come on in.
- Hi.

68
00:03:23,968 --> 00:03:25,068
Go in.

69
00:03:25,268 --> 00:03:26,567
Excuse us.

70
00:03:26,568 --> 00:03:28,338
Some kimchi.

71
00:03:28,738 --> 00:03:30,937
I'll give you some homemade pickled Korean melon...

72
00:03:30,938 --> 00:03:33,638
- Nice.
- and pickled cucumber.

73
00:03:34,248 --> 00:03:35,578
- Korean melon?
- Korean melon.

74
00:03:35,808 --> 00:03:37,078
- Korean melon?
- Yes.

75
00:03:37,848 --> 00:03:39,017
- Pickled?
- Yes.

76
00:03:39,018 --> 00:03:40,547
- Pickled Korean melon.
- I've never had it before.

77
00:03:40,548 --> 00:03:41,817
(Recipe of Korean pickled melon differs by region.)

78
00:03:41,818 --> 00:03:43,217
Pickled Korean melon.

79
00:03:43,218 --> 00:03:44,857
(North Gyeongsang Province's is sweet and salty.)

80
00:03:44,858 --> 00:03:48,357
Just mix it with some sesame oil.

81
00:03:48,358 --> 00:03:49,887
(A generous soul)

82
00:03:49,888 --> 00:03:51,058
And it's done.

83
00:03:51,128 --> 00:03:52,458
- Is that so?
- Yes.

84
00:03:52,698 --> 00:03:54,728
This is a pickled cucumber.

85
00:03:54,998 --> 00:03:58,437
You have to rinse it with water first.

86
00:03:58,438 --> 00:04:00,098
- It's quite salty.
- I see.

87
00:04:02,138 --> 00:04:04,007
Seeing you so often is making me think...

88
00:04:04,008 --> 00:04:05,437
you're one of our old neighbors.

89
00:04:05,438 --> 00:04:06,438
- Right?
- Totally.

90
00:04:06,439 --> 00:04:08,477
We've been here for about two weeks now.

91
00:04:08,478 --> 00:04:09,778
He's been here for three weeks,

92
00:04:09,848 --> 00:04:11,218
so he's practically a villager.

93
00:04:11,378 --> 00:04:13,718
- Yes, a villager.
- It's already been three weeks.

94
00:04:15,788 --> 00:04:16,848
Aged kimchi.

95
00:04:18,058 --> 00:04:19,617
(A bowlful of aged kimchi)

96
00:04:19,618 --> 00:04:20,928
- Is it aged kimchi?
- Yes.

97
00:04:21,688 --> 00:04:22,688
- It looks good.
- Aged kimchi.

98
00:04:22,689 --> 00:04:24,557
- Amazing.
- Does it have to be rinsed?

99
00:04:24,558 --> 00:04:25,658
It can be eaten as is, right?

100
00:04:26,198 --> 00:04:28,297
We eat it as is. Rinsing it would be a waste.

101
00:04:28,298 --> 00:04:29,368
- Exactly.
- Yes.

102
00:04:30,468 --> 00:04:31,797
- It'd be a waste.
- We should make braised kimchi.

103
00:04:31,798 --> 00:04:32,798
Yes.

104
00:04:33,038 --> 00:04:36,037
Buy some pork shoulder meat from the town.

105
00:04:36,038 --> 00:04:37,137
- Pork shoulder meat?
- Yes.

106
00:04:37,138 --> 00:04:38,607
Make kimchi stew with it.

107
00:04:38,608 --> 00:04:39,637
- Pork shoulder meat?
- Yes.

108
00:04:39,638 --> 00:04:40,647
- Pork shoulder meat?
- What's that?

109
00:04:40,648 --> 00:04:41,907
Or just pork arm shoulder.

110
00:04:41,908 --> 00:04:43,747
(Pork shoulder meat or just pork arm shoulder)

111
00:04:43,748 --> 00:04:45,117
- We say pork shoulder meat.
- Pork shoulder meat.

112
00:04:45,118 --> 00:04:46,177
Bon appetit.

113
00:04:46,178 --> 00:04:47,687
- We'll make sure to dig in.
- Thank you.

114
00:04:47,688 --> 00:04:48,818
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

115
00:04:49,488 --> 00:04:51,317
- Have a great day.
- Bye.

116
00:04:51,318 --> 00:04:52,617
- Thank you.
- Bye.

117
00:04:52,618 --> 00:04:54,428
(Going home with bowls of her love)

118
00:04:56,628 --> 00:04:57,697
I didn't think...

119
00:04:57,698 --> 00:04:58,757
- she'd give us so much.
- I know, right?

120
00:04:58,758 --> 00:05:00,598
(A tray full of food)

121
00:05:01,398 --> 00:05:02,427
Is braised kimchi too much...

122
00:05:02,428 --> 00:05:03,428
- for breakfast?
- Yes.

123
00:05:03,768 --> 00:05:05,068
- Right?
- It takes too long.

124
00:05:05,268 --> 00:05:06,338
- Does it?
- Yes.

125
00:05:08,068 --> 00:05:10,408
- Let's make something simple.
- Like what?

126
00:05:11,108 --> 00:05:12,178
What should we make?

127
00:05:15,308 --> 00:05:17,948
(Tasting it right away)

128
00:05:19,778 --> 00:05:20,847
It's so delicious.

129
00:05:20,848 --> 00:05:23,048
(Since they have delicious kimchi)

130
00:05:23,748 --> 00:05:25,718
Let's have breakfast with some fried eggs.

131
00:05:28,828 --> 00:05:31,958
(Today's breakfast is a classic menu.)

132
00:05:33,458 --> 00:05:35,427
(Three)

133
00:05:35,428 --> 00:05:36,897
(Four)

134
00:05:36,898 --> 00:05:38,138
(Five)

135
00:05:39,168 --> 00:05:41,738
(Eggs based on the number of people)

136
00:05:44,708 --> 00:05:47,078
(2 eggs per person)

137
00:05:48,108 --> 00:05:50,048
(Thinking)

138
00:05:50,818 --> 00:05:53,178
(Moving back and forth)

139
00:05:54,248 --> 00:05:55,588
(Whatever.)

140
00:05:56,688 --> 00:05:59,918
(The main chef is generous.)

141
00:06:05,258 --> 00:06:06,958
How many eggs are you frying?

142
00:06:07,598 --> 00:06:09,267
Are we having an egg party?

143
00:06:09,268 --> 00:06:11,338
- We need protein.
- Of course.

144
00:06:13,668 --> 00:06:15,737
(The joggers' balanced protein is done.)

145
00:06:15,738 --> 00:06:16,968
Should we grill some ham?

146
00:06:17,878 --> 00:06:20,238
(Adding in protein that's all about the taste)

147
00:06:26,018 --> 00:06:27,748
- Bread for Tae Ri?
- Bread for Tae Ri.

148
00:06:29,818 --> 00:06:32,658
(We're having ham.)

149
00:06:34,458 --> 00:06:35,788
Rice or bread for Tae Ri?

150
00:06:36,958 --> 00:06:38,028
- Bread.
- Bread.

151
00:06:41,898 --> 00:06:43,097
I don't think Tae Ri will eat.

152
00:06:43,098 --> 00:06:44,438
(We're having spicy braised chicken.)

153
00:06:45,798 --> 00:06:46,937
Bread for Tae Ri?

154
00:06:46,938 --> 00:06:49,208
(Checking again)

155
00:06:50,108 --> 00:06:52,808
(We're having kimchi.)

156
00:06:53,738 --> 00:06:56,477
Honestly, a meal is complete with just rice, eggs, and kimchi.

157
00:06:56,478 --> 00:06:57,478
Totally.

158
00:06:57,479 --> 00:06:59,818
(A hearty breakfast, befitting the lady's kimchi)

159
00:07:00,148 --> 00:07:01,188
All done.

160
00:07:02,218 --> 00:07:04,558
The combination must be good, right?

161
00:07:07,428 --> 00:07:09,288
(Digging in)

162
00:07:10,598 --> 00:07:12,098
(Digging in)

163
00:07:14,128 --> 00:07:15,528
- Good, right?
- Yes.

164
00:07:15,728 --> 00:07:16,967
I missed this. It tastes so good.

165
00:07:16,968 --> 00:07:17,968
(The joggers are fueling up with protein.)

166
00:07:18,198 --> 00:07:19,498
During shoots,

167
00:07:20,968 --> 00:07:22,968
when I have another shoot the next day,

168
00:07:23,308 --> 00:07:25,677
I just get by with some salad.

169
00:07:25,678 --> 00:07:26,678
I see.

170
00:07:27,138 --> 00:07:28,577
But here, I'm barely gaining weight despite eating.

171
00:07:28,578 --> 00:07:29,648
- Right?
- Yes.

172
00:07:29,808 --> 00:07:30,948
We must be exhausted.

173
00:07:32,618 --> 00:07:33,677
It's interesting.

174
00:07:33,678 --> 00:07:35,748
(With that said, eating another mouthful)

175
00:07:37,218 --> 00:07:39,758
(Meanwhile, Tae Ri has freshened up.)

176
00:07:40,958 --> 00:07:42,558
- Tae Ri.
- Yes?

177
00:07:43,558 --> 00:07:44,758
We toasted some bread.

178
00:07:45,098 --> 00:07:46,328
You toasted bread?

179
00:07:46,598 --> 00:07:48,028
I thought you wouldn't eat rice.

180
00:07:49,068 --> 00:07:50,468
- Thank you.
- Of course.

181
00:07:51,538 --> 00:07:52,997
- It's so good.
- Right?

182
00:07:52,998 --> 00:07:54,738
(Already finished his bowl)

183
00:07:55,768 --> 00:07:57,778
(Disappointed)

184
00:07:58,678 --> 00:08:00,478
How about we share a bowl of rice?

185
00:08:00,778 --> 00:08:02,748
- Shall we?
- If you can eat more.

186
00:08:02,948 --> 00:08:04,348
I think I can.

187
00:08:06,418 --> 00:08:08,818
(Tae Ri starts with an egg.)

188
00:08:09,388 --> 00:08:11,188
Sunny speed... What was it again?

189
00:08:11,418 --> 00:08:12,918
- Sunny side up.
- Sunny side up.

190
00:08:13,318 --> 00:08:15,388
- Sunny speed.
- Does it suddenly get speedy?

191
00:08:15,688 --> 00:08:17,458
(Laughing)

192
00:08:20,198 --> 00:08:23,128
(As expected, Tae Ri eats bread.)

193
00:08:24,868 --> 00:08:28,438
(We're eating rice.)

194
00:08:30,508 --> 00:08:34,078
(Another healthy homemade meal today)

195
00:08:35,648 --> 00:08:36,808
The kimchi is amazing.

196
00:08:37,378 --> 00:08:39,148
- Tae Ri, have you tried the kimchi?
- No.

197
00:08:39,348 --> 00:08:40,688
- Is it that kimchi?
- Yes.

198
00:08:40,788 --> 00:08:43,388
- The one from the old lady.
- Will it taste good with toast?

199
00:08:44,218 --> 00:08:46,158
Just try a piece of it.

200
00:08:48,258 --> 00:08:49,427
(Shocked)

201
00:08:49,428 --> 00:08:50,797
- It's delicious, right?
- Yes.

202
00:08:50,798 --> 00:08:52,028
- It's different, right?
- Totally.

203
00:08:52,128 --> 00:08:53,157
- It's different. Must be...
- Yes.

204
00:08:53,158 --> 00:08:54,628
- Mungyeong's kimchi.
- Yes.

205
00:08:55,198 --> 00:08:56,368
- It's so good.
- Right?

206
00:08:59,538 --> 00:09:01,338
What an amazing weather today.

207
00:09:05,178 --> 00:09:08,078
(Writing replies to the question notes before class)

208
00:09:08,678 --> 00:09:10,378
Kyung Mo? I wonder what he wrote.

209
00:09:10,478 --> 00:09:11,518
Kyung Mo.

210
00:09:12,178 --> 00:09:14,188
"I'll see you on the last day, Tiger Teacher."

211
00:09:16,418 --> 00:09:20,587
(Kyung Mo's warning)

212
00:09:20,588 --> 00:09:21,657
Tiger...

213
00:09:21,658 --> 00:09:24,927
(The person who is replying kindly...)

214
00:09:24,928 --> 00:09:27,158
(is Tiger... No, North Pole Teacher.)

215
00:09:27,968 --> 00:09:29,727
(Tiger Teacher is a scary teacher.)

216
00:09:29,728 --> 00:09:31,537
(It's best if he doesn't show up. Be careful.)

217
00:09:31,538 --> 00:09:32,997
(Saying the lines with confidence is great.)

218
00:09:32,998 --> 00:09:34,237
(Puppies are cool and cute.)

219
00:09:34,238 --> 00:09:35,668
(Our cute Kyung Mo can also pull it off! From North Pole Teacher)

220
00:09:36,968 --> 00:09:38,238
What did the kids write?

221
00:09:39,438 --> 00:09:41,547
"How many times do you read..."

222
00:09:41,548 --> 00:09:43,077
"the script when practicing?"

223
00:09:43,078 --> 00:09:44,278
(Multiple times is okay.)

224
00:09:44,718 --> 00:09:46,048
Is she talking about drama scripts?

225
00:09:46,718 --> 00:09:48,148
We read it countless times.

226
00:09:49,848 --> 00:09:52,688
(Warm-hearted Potato Teacher writes the reply.)

227
00:09:56,288 --> 00:09:57,958
(Sliding)

228
00:09:59,098 --> 00:10:01,028
"Countless times."

229
00:10:01,668 --> 00:10:02,668
What?

230
00:10:02,669 --> 00:10:04,637
- Why are you embarrassed?
- Stop it.

231
00:10:04,638 --> 00:10:06,538
What's wrong with you? Stop what?

232
00:10:06,698 --> 00:10:08,638
What's the big deal when it'll be revealed either way?

233
00:10:09,368 --> 00:10:10,437
"Countless times."

234
00:10:10,438 --> 00:10:11,677
(Trying again)

235
00:10:11,678 --> 00:10:14,178
Stop it. Why are you reading it out loud?

236
00:10:15,208 --> 00:10:16,948
I'll read it with my eyes only.

237
00:10:18,248 --> 00:10:19,718
"Countless times."

238
00:10:20,018 --> 00:10:21,518
- "Keep going..." - Stop.

239
00:10:21,588 --> 00:10:22,817
- Stop it.
- Why?

240
00:10:22,818 --> 00:10:23,818
- For real.
- Why are you embarrassed?

241
00:10:23,819 --> 00:10:24,857
Your ears are beet red.

242
00:10:24,858 --> 00:10:26,418
- No, stop.
- How come?

243
00:10:26,888 --> 00:10:29,627
Fine. I'll read it monotone. I read it with too much emotion.

244
00:10:29,628 --> 00:10:30,758
That must be why.

245
00:10:32,158 --> 00:10:34,668
"Reading it repeatedly..."

246
00:10:37,068 --> 00:10:38,768
Ju Eun will read it.

247
00:10:40,398 --> 00:10:41,638
Why are you...

248
00:10:41,808 --> 00:10:44,338
You can give advice as an acting senior.

249
00:10:44,778 --> 00:10:46,677
- No.
- You're hilarious.

250
00:10:46,678 --> 00:10:49,178
(Shy Potato is embarrassed about giving advice.)

251
00:10:49,808 --> 00:10:51,177
(Revealing the answer)

252
00:10:51,178 --> 00:10:52,677
(Countless times. Keep going, and you can do it!)

253
00:10:52,678 --> 00:10:54,148
Okay. Are we done?

254
00:10:54,948 --> 00:10:56,647
- Ha Yun.
- Right, Ha Yun.

255
00:10:56,648 --> 00:10:58,317
Give me Ha Yun's. I'm curious.

256
00:10:58,318 --> 00:10:59,918
- Ha Yun is...
- Ha Yun?

257
00:11:00,318 --> 00:11:01,727
"How did Mr. Kangnam..."

258
00:11:01,728 --> 00:11:04,498
"and Potato Teacher have good chemistry yesterday?"

259
00:11:05,258 --> 00:11:07,258
What chemistry did we have?

260
00:11:07,528 --> 00:11:09,928
Did we have good chemistry while acting?

261
00:11:11,168 --> 00:11:13,138
Or did we have bad chemistry?

262
00:11:15,568 --> 00:11:17,577
- If you had good chemistry.
- "Did you have good chemistry?"

263
00:11:17,578 --> 00:11:18,807
He's asking us.

264
00:11:18,808 --> 00:11:20,477
- A question for both of us.
- How...

265
