00:21:00,888 --> 00:21:02,528
- Oil him.
- Oil him.

532
00:21:03,358 --> 00:21:05,858
He's free! Yes!

533
00:21:05,958 --> 00:21:08,128
You guys are really kind!

534
00:21:08,498 --> 00:21:10,268
I may look like I'm made of tin,

535
00:21:10,668 --> 00:21:11,968
but I used to be a human.

536
00:21:12,298 --> 00:21:16,068
We heard that the Wizard of Oz would grant any wish,

537
00:21:16,408 --> 00:21:17,508
so we were on our way there.

538
00:21:17,608 --> 00:21:20,578
Then, I'm going to wish for a heart.

539
00:21:20,938 --> 00:21:24,048
I want to have a warm heart and live a happy life.

540
00:21:24,148 --> 00:21:26,778
Tin Man, you should join us!

541
00:21:27,118 --> 00:21:28,188
- Yes!
- Join us!

542
00:21:28,618 --> 00:21:31,517
We move on to the Lion's scene.

543
00:21:31,518 --> 00:21:32,518
The Lion.

544
00:21:33,318 --> 00:21:36,327
(Toto and Dorothy)

545
00:21:36,328 --> 00:21:37,728
- Roar!
- Yelp!

546
00:21:38,198 --> 00:21:39,198
Toto!

547
00:21:40,598 --> 00:21:42,898
(Dorothy runs and hits the Lion on the nose.)

548
00:21:43,328 --> 00:21:44,837
(Laughing)

549
00:21:44,838 --> 00:21:46,138
Oh, my nose!

550
00:21:46,338 --> 00:21:49,837
(He starts crying after the hit.)

551
00:21:49,838 --> 00:21:51,507
I'm actually a coward.

552
00:21:51,508 --> 00:21:53,237
(The Lion turned out to be cowardly.)

553
00:21:53,238 --> 00:21:55,608
Hey, Lion.

554
00:21:56,308 --> 00:21:58,778
We're on our way to the Wizard of Oz to make our wish.

555
00:21:58,978 --> 00:22:00,448
Do you want to join us?

556
00:22:00,678 --> 00:22:01,988
I'll come with you.

557
00:22:02,588 --> 00:22:06,288
I can no longer handle living without courage.

558
00:22:06,488 --> 00:22:08,358
Let's go together!

559
00:22:08,828 --> 00:22:10,188
- Yes!
- Yes!

560
00:22:10,488 --> 00:22:13,527
- All right, that's all.
- That's it.

561
00:22:13,528 --> 00:22:17,097
Now, please step forward if you're in the scene...

562
00:22:17,098 --> 00:22:19,337
- for the Tin Man and the Lion.
- Come on out.

563
00:22:19,338 --> 00:22:21,707
This time, we'll help.

564
00:22:21,708 --> 00:22:23,437
- We're doing it twice.
- Come on out.

565
00:22:23,438 --> 00:22:25,938
But we won't be there the second time.

566
00:22:26,338 --> 00:22:28,408
You're on your own the second time.

567
00:22:28,778 --> 00:22:30,707
- Did you see the Tin Man scene?
- Yes.

568
00:22:30,708 --> 00:22:32,817
You can do better than I did.

569
00:22:32,818 --> 00:22:35,247
- No, I can't.
- No, be confident.

570
00:22:35,248 --> 00:22:36,647
I didn't practice that much.

571
00:22:36,648 --> 00:22:38,317
Just be confident. You did the movements well.

572
00:22:38,318 --> 00:22:39,818
Just do it like that, okay?

573
00:22:40,018 --> 00:22:42,028
- Okay.
- Just do it however you want.

574
00:22:43,428 --> 00:22:45,658
- Let's give it a go.
- Let's start.

575
00:22:46,198 --> 00:22:48,158
Shall we get going, then?

576
00:22:48,268 --> 00:22:50,267
- Yes!
- Go around!

577
00:22:50,268 --> 00:22:52,167
Let's go. There you go.

578
00:22:52,168 --> 00:22:53,438
(The adventure begins with the Scarecrow.)

579
00:22:54,238 --> 00:22:55,307
(The Tin Man appears.)

580
00:22:55,308 --> 00:22:56,338
Toto, stop!

581
00:22:56,438 --> 00:22:58,478
- Grunt, grunt.
- Sniff, sniff.

582
00:22:58,578 --> 00:23:01,978
- Grunt, grunt.
- Sniff, sniff. I smell something.

583
00:23:02,078 --> 00:23:05,077
Grunt, grunt. Hi. Will you help me?

584
00:23:05,078 --> 00:23:06,617
Surround the Tin Man, everyone!

585
00:23:06,618 --> 00:23:07,618
All right.

586
00:23:07,619 --> 00:23:08,887
- Oil him.
- Okay.

587
00:23:08,888 --> 00:23:11,147
Oil his joints. Now, go back.

588
00:23:11,148 --> 00:23:12,517
- Go back.
- Okay.

589
00:23:12,518 --> 00:23:13,888
Good. And then...

590
00:23:14,288 --> 00:23:16,927
You guys are really kind.

591
00:23:16,928 --> 00:23:20,028
I may look like I'm made of tin, but I used to be a human.

592
00:23:20,198 --> 00:23:21,198
All right!

593
00:23:22,198 --> 00:23:27,468
We heard that the Wizard of Oz would grant any wish.

594
00:23:29,108 --> 00:23:31,408
So, we were on our way there.

595
00:23:31,878 --> 00:23:33,137
(Well done!)

596
00:23:33,138 --> 00:23:34,608
Now, Toto appears.

597
00:23:35,478 --> 00:23:36,907
And Toto growls.

598
00:23:36,908 --> 00:23:38,347
You look around because you're scared.

599
00:23:38,348 --> 00:23:40,678
All right, it's your turn.

600
00:23:41,018 --> 00:23:42,588
- Roar!
- Yelp!

601
00:23:42,988 --> 00:23:44,487
- Dorothy!
- Dorothy, it's the Lion!

602
00:23:44,488 --> 00:23:45,588
Toto!

603
00:23:45,858 --> 00:23:47,488
- Hit him.
- Hit him!

604
00:23:47,788 --> 00:23:48,858
(Smacking)

605
00:23:49,088 --> 00:23:50,927
- Now, you fall, Won Jin.
- You fall.

606
00:23:50,928 --> 00:23:52,257
- On the ground.
- Look up.

607
00:23:52,258 --> 00:23:53,528
Look up.

608
00:23:53,598 --> 00:23:55,567
Get away from Toto!

609
00:23:55,568 --> 00:23:56,827
Kids, stand behind her.

610
00:23:56,828 --> 00:23:57,897
(What was the next line?)

611
00:23:57,898 --> 00:23:58,967
(No matter how scary you are, I will fight for Toto.)

612
00:23:58,968 --> 00:23:59,968
"No matter how."

613
00:23:59,969 --> 00:24:03,368
No matter how scary you are, I will fight for Toto!

614
00:24:05,008 --> 00:24:06,277
Now, Tin Man.

615
00:24:06,278 --> 00:24:07,538
(The Tin Man's turn)

616
00:24:07,608 --> 00:24:08,747
What was it?

617
00:24:08,748 --> 00:24:11,348
(What was it?)

618
00:24:11,778 --> 00:24:12,848
"Though I don't have a heart."

619
00:24:13,318 --> 00:24:15,748
Though I don't have a heart, this breaks my heart.

620
00:24:16,018 --> 00:24:18,147
- Lion... Hi.
- "Hey."

621
00:24:18,148 --> 00:24:19,388
Hey, Lion!

622
00:24:20,088 --> 00:24:23,027
We're on our way to the Wizard of Oz to make our wish.

623
00:24:23,028 --> 00:24:24,558
Do you want to join us?

624
00:24:25,528 --> 00:24:28,258
Will he give me courage, then?

625
00:24:28,768 --> 00:24:30,727
Let's go and find him.

626
00:24:30,728 --> 00:24:32,497
The starting pose on the count of three.

627
00:24:32,498 --> 00:24:33,868
One, two, three!

628
00:24:33,998 --> 00:24:35,307
- Yes!
- Yes!

629
00:24:35,308 --> 00:24:37,538
That was one rep.

630
00:24:37,638 --> 00:24:40,537
We helped out a lot, right?

631
00:24:40,538 --> 00:24:42,747
This time, we won't help you.

632
00:24:42,748 --> 00:24:45,518
- I want you to do it on your own.
- Okay.

633
00:24:45,978 --> 00:24:47,077
Do exactly what we just did.

634
00:24:47,078 --> 00:24:50,387
- We're spectators now.
- I can't do it, then!

635
00:24:50,388 --> 00:24:52,857
- Yes, you can.
- You have to follow through.

636
00:24:52,858 --> 00:24:54,588
But I didn't practice enough.

637
00:24:54,818 --> 00:24:56,487
Can you help us out a little?

638
00:24:56,488 --> 00:24:58,287
- Maybe a little.
- Just a little.

639
00:24:58,288 --> 00:25:00,397
We're going to help you a little, though.

640
00:25:00,398 --> 00:25:02,097
- Let's go as far as you can.
- Of course.

641
00:25:02,098 --> 00:25:03,768
- It's okay to make mistakes.
- Let's start. Action.

642
00:25:03,998 --> 00:25:05,237
(Attempt number 2, the Tin Man scene)

643
00:25:05,238 --> 00:25:08,367
- Grunt, grunt.
- Sniff, sniff. I smell something.

644
00:25:08,368 --> 00:25:12,108
Grunt, grunt. Hi. Will you help me?

645
00:25:13,008 --> 00:25:14,638
How should we help?

646
00:25:14,738 --> 00:25:18,718
There's an oil can at my waist. Please oil my joints.

647
00:25:19,848 --> 00:25:21,718
What? Wicked Witch of the West?

648
00:25:23,348 --> 00:25:26,757
Before the Witch shows up,

649
00:25:26,758 --> 00:25:30,227
we'll get to the Wizard of Oz...

650
00:25:30,228 --> 00:25:31,228
(And ask him to send us home!)

651
00:25:31,229 --> 00:25:32,357
"Home."

652
00:25:32,358 --> 00:25:34,558
And ask him to send us home!

653
00:25:34,658 --> 00:25:37,497
I need a brain, so I'm going to ask him...

654
00:25:37,498 --> 00:25:39,367
for a brain.

655
00:25:39,368 --> 00:25:41,167
Then, I'll ask for a heart.

656
00:25:41,168 --> 00:25:42,737
No, he still has more lines.

657
00:25:42,738 --> 00:25:44,437
- Oh, really?
- "You should also..."

658
00:25:44,438 --> 00:25:47,477
You should also go to the Wizard...

659
00:25:47,478 --> 00:25:48,748
"Make a wish."

660
00:25:49,108 --> 00:25:51,108
- "And make a wish." - And make a wish!

661
00:25:51,448 --> 00:25:54,577
Then, I'm going to ask for a heart.

662
00:25:54,578 --> 00:25:57,287
I want to have a warm heart...

663
00:25:57,288 --> 00:25:58,517
Listen carefully, kids.

664
00:25:58,518 --> 00:25:59,817
And live a happy life.

665
00:25:59,818 --> 00:26:01,118
He wants to live a happy life.

666
00:26:01,158 --> 00:26:03,088
Look over there!

667
00:26:03,988 --> 00:26:06,058
That's a very dangerous forest.

668
00:26:07,028 --> 00:26:08,468
What do we do?

669
00:26:08,598 --> 00:26:10,998
- "It's so dangerous." - It's so dangerous...

670
00:26:12,168 --> 00:26:14,697
- "That we can't pass." - that we can't pass.

671
00:26:14,698 --> 00:26:15,708
(They push on, thanks to the teachers.)

672
00:26:15,968 --> 00:26:18,208
Tin Man,

673
00:26:18,268 --> 00:26:20,707
will you go and...

674
00:26:20,708 --> 00:26:22,608
- "Chop down those trees." - chop down those trees?

675
00:26:22,848 --> 00:26:25,278
I don't have a heart, but I know how to chop down trees.

676
00:26:26,678 --> 00:26:27,678
Chop!

677
00:26:27,878 --> 00:26:28,948
- Yes!
- Thrilled.

678
00:26:29,148 --> 00:26:30,948
- Chop!
- Thrilled again.

679
00:26:31,018 --> 00:26:32,758
Everyone leaves the stage.

680
00:26:33,118 --> 00:26:35,288
- Toto.
- You're the best!

681
00:26:35,828 --> 00:26:37,288
(He's so cute!)

682
00:26:37,388 --> 00:26:41,427
- Now, it's the Lion's scene.
- This is very important.

683
00:26:41,428 --> 00:26:42,968
Go hard.

684
00:26:43,368 --> 00:26:45,167
It's the bell.

685
00:26:45,168 --> 00:26:46,867
(Recess begins at that moment.)

686
00:26:46,868 --> 00:26:47,898
Recess!

687
00:26:48,808 --> 00:26:51,707
Let's play soccer!

688
00:26:51,708 --> 00:26:54,838
Kids, I don't think you memorized all the lines.

689
00:26:55,778 --> 00:26:57,577
Let's memorize them properly, okay?

690
00:26:57,578 --> 00:26:58,917
You have to memorize them now.

691
00:26:58,918 --> 00:27:00,647
I want to play too.

692
00:27:00,648 --> 00:27:01,947
- Okay.
- Let's play together.

693
00:27:01,948 --> 00:27:02,988
(They're too busy playing to hear her.)

694
00:27:04,148 --> 00:27:07,158
(Meanwhile, Do Hyun...)

695
00:27:10,428 --> 00:27:12,258
Do Hyun, what's up?

696
00:27:13,358 --> 00:27:15,168
What makes you so uncertain?

697
00:27:15,598 --> 00:27:17,628
You did great at first.

698
00:27:17,728 --> 00:27:18,867
You don't feel so confident?

699
00:27:18,868 --> 00:27:20,098
Because you didn't memorize the lines, or what?

700
00:27:20,468 --> 00:27:21,498
Why are you crying?

701
00:27:22,168 --> 00:27:24,038
What's the problem?

702
00:27:24,768 --> 00:27:26,377
What's wrong?

703
00:27:26,378 --> 00:27:27,807
(Do Hyun bursts into tears.)

704
00:27:27,808 --> 00:27:29,007
Why are you crying?

705
00:27:29,008 --> 00:27:30,408
Why are you crying? You did great.

706
00:27:33,048 --> 00:27:34,678
I want to do well, but...

707
00:27:34,718 --> 00:27:37,118
- But?
- I couldn't memorize it.

708
00:27:37,218 --> 00:27:38,658
Oh, you just want to do a good job.

709
00:27:38,858 --> 00:27:40,918
- We still have time.
- Really?

710
00:27:41,318 --> 00:27:44,057
- We still have time.
- But you're doing amazing.

711
00:27:44,058 --> 00:27:46,297
You're the best one right now. What are you saying?

712
00:27:46,298 --> 00:27:47,727
Yes, you're killing it.

713
00:27:47,728 --> 00:27:50,498
Also, doing well...

714
00:27:51,128 --> 00:27:54,237
Having fun is more important than doing a good job.

715
00:27:54,238 --> 00:27:55,267
- Yes.
- Yes.

716
00:27:55,268 --> 00:27:57,867
Doing the Tin Man's movements...

717
00:27:57,868 --> 00:27:59,107
- is fun, right?
- Yes.

718
00:27:59,108 --> 00:28:00,707
- And expressing yourself.
- Yes.

719
00:28:00,708 --> 00:28:03,007
- Acting is fun, right?
- Yes.

720
00:28:03,008 --> 00:28:05,778
And I can tell that you're having the most fun.

721
00:28:06,048 --> 00:28:07,348
Okay.

722
00:28:07,818 --> 00:28:10,247
- Having fun is your job.
- Okay.

723
00:28:10,248 --> 00:28:12,318
- Don't be too burdened, okay?
- Okay.

724
00:28:14,018 --> 00:28:18,697
When Do Hyun cried because he did poorly...

725
00:28:18,698 --> 00:28:19,998
when he wanted to do well...

726
00:28:20,198 --> 00:28:21,868
He doesn't have to feel that way,

727
00:28:22,998 --> 00:28:25,538
but I'm also like that.

728
00:28:27,138 --> 00:28:28,267
I want to do a good job,

729
00:28:28,268 --> 00:28:30,568
and I've always thought I wasn't good enough.

730
00:28:31,238 --> 00:28:34,008
My reality has always...

731
00:28:34,378 --> 00:28:36,708
fallen short of my ideals.

732
00:28:38,208 --> 00:28:41,448
But I couldn't speak...

733
00:28:42,718 --> 00:28:44,487
because all my words...

734
00:28:44,488 --> 00:28:45,787
(What she realized after reflecting on herself)

735
00:28:45,788 --> 00:28:47,918
felt contradictory.

736
00:28:51,758 --> 00:28:54,027
How many times have I told the kids,

737
00:28:54,028 --> 00:28:55,698
"You have to do it well?"

738
00:28:55,868 --> 00:28:57,528
I bet it was a lot.

739
00:28:57,728 --> 00:28:58,738
So, that's...

740
00:29:00,368 --> 00:29:03,337
(She worries that she might have put pressure on them...)

741
00:29:03,338 --> 00:29:04,907
(without meaning to.)

742
00:29:04,908 --> 00:29:06,937
I don't know how to explain.

743
00:29:06,938 --> 00:29:08,648
Finding the right words...

744
00:29:08,848 --> 00:29:10,877
in every situation...

745
00:29:10,878 --> 00:29:13,418
Finding that is so...

746
00:29:14,578 --> 00:29:15,687
difficult.

747
00:29:15,688 --> 00:29:17,418
(The seventh class ends, leaving her much to think about.)

748
00:29:20,188 --> 00:29:22,357
This is the eighth class.

749
00:29:22,358 --> 00:29:24,388
(8th class)

750
00:29:24,858 --> 00:29:27,528
Kids, the teachers stayed up all night...

751
00:29:27,928 --> 00:29:30,697
to make your stage props.

752
00:29:30,698 --> 00:29:31,698
(Handmade stage props)

753
00:29:31,699 --> 00:29:34,068
It looks legitimate. I think we can attach more.

754
00:29:34,368 --> 00:29:35,368
They'll love it, right?

755
00:29:37,438 --> 00:29:40,908
(North Pole Teacher is working from home.)

756
00:29:41,808 --> 00:29:44,078
- Does it look plausible?
- Very.

757
00:29:44,248 --> 00:29:45,447
- It does?
- Yes.

758
00:29:45,448 --> 00:29:46,448
(Proud)

759
00:29:46,618 --> 00:29:48,948
(He worked from home in the morning.)

760
00:29:49,418 --> 00:29:51,588
- That's hot.
- Careful.

761
00:29:51,918 --> 00:29:54,157
- That's really hot.
- You have to be careful.

762
00:29:54,158 --> 00:29:55,588
(He sacrificed his fingers for these.)

763
00:29:57,258 --> 00:29:58,258
(North Pole Teacher's ambitious work)

764
00:29:58,259 --> 00:29:59,458
That's so cute.

765
00:29:59,598 --> 00:30:00,658
Is this dangling one okay?

766
00:30:01,028 --> 00:30:03,328
- The Tin Man's axe.
- The Tin Man's axe!

767
00:30:03,698 --> 00:30:05,638
- This is the Munchkin's hat.
- Gosh.

768
00:30:06,568 --> 00:30:08,337
A hat for Munchkin.

769
00:30:08,338 --> 00:30:09,538
(It's mine.)

770
00:30:10,838 --> 00:30:12,508
You're so scary.

771
00:30:13,138 --> 00:30:14,207
Do you need help with the ribbon?

772
00:30:14,208 --> 00:30:15,507
(Dorothy's look is complete with the ribbon.)

773
00:30:15,508 --> 00:30:17,448
Put your bangs up. You were adorable yesterday.

774
00:30:18,878 --> 00:30:20,317
(Helping her out)

775
00:30:20,318 --> 00:30:21,377
Okay!

776
00:30:21,378 --> 00:30:23,287
It's perfect for you. Let's go.

777
00:30:23,288 --> 00:30:24,317
- She looks good, doesn't she?
- Yes!

778
00:30:24,318 --> 00:30:26,387
- She's adorable.
- Let's get going.

779
00:30:26,388 --> 00:30:27,758
So pretty. Let's start.

780
00:30:28,588 --> 00:30:31,887
Kids, we're going to go from the very first scene...

781
00:30:31,888 --> 00:30:34,797
to the final scene without stopping.

782
00:30:34,798 --> 00:30:36,367
But don't you worry.

783
00:30:36,368 --> 00:30:39,037
The teachers will be there to help you out.

784
00:30:39,038 --> 00:30:41,697
I want to know what you thought about our process.

785
00:30:41,698 --> 00:30:43,838
Lion, what did you think?

786
00:30:44,868 --> 00:30:46,007
It was fun.

787
00:30:46,008 --> 00:30:48,277
It was fun. Were there any difficult parts?

788
00:30:48,278 --> 00:30:49,747
- No.
- No?

789
00:30:49,748 --> 00:30:51,348
- No.
- No difficult parts?

790
00:30:52,448 --> 00:30:53,617
It was confusing.

791
00:30:53,618 --> 00:30:55,517
Good. I like your honesty.

792
00:30:55,518 --> 00:30:56,818
- Now, Hyo Min.
- Hyo Min.

793
00:30:57,748 --> 00:30:59,287
- I'll be honest.
- Yes.

794
00:30:59,288 --> 00:31:00,858
- It's difficult.
- Is it?

795
00:31:01,058 --> 00:31:02,927
- It can be difficult.
- It can be difficult.

796
00:31:02,928 --> 00:31:06,357
We would love to help you...

797
00:31:06,358 --> 00:31:07,698
with the difficult parts.

798
00:31:08,098 --> 00:31:09,567
What's the most difficult part, Hyo Min?

799
00:31:09,568 --> 00:31:11,398
Do you want me to shorten your lines?

800
00:31:11,568 --> 00:31:13,068
- Then...
- Not that?

801
00:31:13,338 --> 00:31:14,637
Don't think about it as memorizing.

802
00:31:14,638 --> 00:31:18,007
You already know all the moves by the Scarecrow, right?

803
00:31:18,008 --> 00:31:20,008
- Yes, so do it freely.
- Hyo Min.

804
00:31:20,808 --> 00:31:23,107
Next, Ju Eun, what was narrating like?

805
00:31:23,108 --> 00:31:25,977
I wish I could act with more confidence...

806
00:31:25,978 --> 00:31:27,847
and speak up.

807
00:31:27,848 --> 00:31:29,047
Yes.

808
00:31:29,048 --> 00:31:30,487
Let's speak up, everyone.

809
00:31:30,488 --> 00:31:31,817
In 1, 2, 3.

810
00:31:31,818 --> 00:31:34,117
- Speak up!
- Speak up!

811
00:31:34,118 --> 00:31:36,187
Okay. Should we take it from the top?

812
00:31:36,188 --> 00:31:37,358
From the top, guys.

813
00:31:38,388 --> 00:31:40,658
Narrator, begin.

814
00:31:40,828 --> 00:31:43,667
A girl named Dorothy lived in Mungyeong.

815
00:31:43,668 --> 00:31:47,837
Her house was carried away by a whirlwind,

816
00:31:47,838 --> 00:31:49,537
and she landed...

817
00:31:49,538 --> 00:31:51,207
in the strange and magical Land of Oz,

818
00:31:51,208 --> 00:31:52,838
along with her little dog, Toto.

819
00:31:53,908 --> 00:31:55,848
Dorothy, appear.

820
00:31:56,548 --> 00:31:58,978
Goodness! This isn't Mungyeong!

821
00:31:59,278 --> 00:32:02,018
It's so brilliant and colorful!

822
00:32:03,548 --> 00:32:06,657
- It's dazzling!
- It's dazzling!

823
00:32:06,658 --> 00:32:09,888
- Sniff, sniff. I smell flowers.
- Sniff, sniff. I smell flowers.

824
00:32:11,458 --> 00:32:13,928
- I'm talking!
- Toto is talking!

825
00:32:14,628 --> 00:32:17,028
Wizard, where are you from?

826
00:32:17,168 --> 00:32:18,527
Where are we?

827
00:32:18,528 --> 00:32:20,237
This is Oz.

828
00:32:20,238 --> 00:32:23,507
(Watch out for the Wicked Witch of the West.)

829
00:32:23,508 --> 00:32:24,567
"Watch out for the Wicked Witch of the West."

830
00:32:24,568 --> 00:32:26,208
Watch out for the Wicked Witch of the West.

831
00:32:26,338 --> 00:32:28,708
I want to go back home.

832
00:32:29,508 --> 00:32:32,218
Why don't you go to the Wizard of Oz?

833
00:32:32,278 --> 00:32:35,217
Wear these shoes. These belong to the Witch.

834
00:32:35,218 --> 00:32:38,517
And I'll give this cute puppy a necktie.

835
00:32:38,518 --> 00:32:39,687
Toto is thrilled!

836
00:32:39,688 --> 00:32:41,758
(Thrilled)

837
00:32:42,288 --> 00:32:43,788
Munchkin leaves.

838
00:32:44,358 --> 00:32:45,557
Let's go, Toto!

839
00:32:45,558 --> 00:32:47,497
Let's go together.

840
00:32:47,498 --> 00:32:48,528
Yes!

841
00:32:49,428 --> 00:32:51,498
The curtain closes.

842
00:32:51,898 --> 00:32:54,598
Scarecrow, where's the step?

843
00:32:55,098 --> 00:32:57,568
Yes, get the step.

844
00:32:59,678 --> 00:33:01,377
Climb, and say your lines.

845
00:33:01,378 --> 00:33:02,907
(It's the scene where Hyo Min, the Scarecrow, appears.)

846
00:33:02,908 --> 00:33:04,707
The curtain opens!

847
00:33:04,708 --> 00:33:06,147
The sound of crows!

848
00:33:06,148 --> 00:33:08,578
Caw!

849
00:33:09,448 --> 00:33:13,087
These birds aren't afraid of me anymore.

850
00:33:13,088 --> 00:33:14,088
All right!

851
00:33:14,418 --> 00:33:15,487
You're doing great, Hyo Min!

852
00:33:15,488 --> 00:33:17,588
(They see the Scarecrow on a pole.)

853
00:33:17,688 --> 00:33:19,898
Hi, what lovely weather.

854
00:33:20,398 --> 00:33:22,797
- The crows aren't...
- Hyo Min!

855
00:33:22,798 --> 00:33:24,228
Can you speak up a little?

856
00:33:25,228 --> 00:33:26,838
You can do it.

857
00:33:27,468 --> 00:33:30,067
The crows aren't even scared of me.

858
00:33:30,068 --> 00:33:31,908
Thanks for talking to me.

859
00:33:32,738 --> 00:33:34,438
Can't you come down?

860
00:33:34,578 --> 00:33:36,747
I can't get down by myself.

861
00:33:36,748 --> 00:33:38,948
There's a pole on my back.

862
00:33:40,078 --> 00:33:41,918
I'll help you down.

863
00:33:43,188 --> 00:33:44,248
Two, three.

864
00:33:44,918 --> 00:33:46,817
(Plopping)

865
00:33:46,818 --> 00:33:48,888
- Hi.
- Now, politely say hi.

866
00:33:49,488 --> 00:33:50,488
Hi.

867
00:33:50,928 --> 00:33:53,058
Let me say hi again. Hi.

868
00:33:53,628 --> 00:33:54,628
I'm...

869
00:33:56,798 --> 00:33:57,998
I want to hear you from here.

870
00:33:59,338 --> 00:34:00,538
"I'm made of..."

871
00:34:00,698 --> 00:34:03,067
I'm made of straws...

872
00:34:03,068 --> 00:34:04,508
I forgot the straws.

873
00:34:16,488 --> 00:34:17,488
All right.

874
00:34:18,188 --> 00:34:21,288
I'm made of straws,

875
00:34:21,618 --> 00:34:23,528
so I don't exist.

876
00:34:24,228 --> 00:34:25,428
"I don't know who I am."

877
00:34:25,558 --> 00:34:27,158
Oh, I don't know who I am.

878
00:34:28,528 --> 00:34:29,567
(Who are you?)

879
00:34:29,568 --> 00:34:30,928
Ask your friends.

880
00:34:32,068 --> 00:34:33,968
(Struggling)

881
00:34:34,168 --> 00:34:36,238
- "Who are you?" - Who are you?

882
00:34:36,668 --> 00:34:38,768
I'm Dorothy, and he's Toto.

883
00:34:39,378 --> 00:34:40,907
(I'm going to the Emerald Castle,)

884
00:34:40,908 --> 00:34:43,307
(so I can go back to my house in Mungyeong!)

885
00:34:43,308 --> 00:34:45,948
I'm going to the Emerald Castle,

886
00:34:46,248 --> 00:34:49,448
so I can go back to my house in Mungyeong.

887
00:34:50,448 --> 00:34:54,357
- Emerald...
- The Wizard of Oz...

888
00:34:54,358 --> 00:34:58,388
will grant all our wishes.

889
00:34:58,458 --> 00:35:00,198
Oz? The Wizard?

890
00:35:00,328 --> 00:35:02,368
Wishes? What's a wish?

891
00:35:02,698 --> 00:35:04,027
You don't know what that is?

892
00:35:04,028 --> 00:35:05,638
I don't know...

893
00:35:06,738 --> 00:35:09,768
(The play keeps stopping.)

894
00:35:10,238 --> 00:35:13,738
"Is our class boring?"

895
00:35:14,678 --> 00:35:17,507
"It must be boring for them." I've been thinking that.

896
00:35:17,508 --> 00:35:18,907
(Watching those kids...)

897
00:35:18,908 --> 00:35:20,848
I'm a teacher here,

898
00:35:21,648 --> 00:35:24,348
so I feel like I should put in the work...

899
00:35:24,488 --> 00:35:26,517
and teach them as much as...

900
00:35:26,518 --> 00:35:30,528
I mean, everything's new to us. Including myself.

901
00:35:31,288 --> 00:35:35,398
I'm not exactly sure how to explain it to them.

902
00:35:36,698 --> 00:35:39,438
Guys, how do you want your play to be?

903
00:35:39,598 --> 00:35:40,738
Fun.

904
00:35:41,698 --> 00:35:43,707
- Fun, right?
- Yes.

905
00:35:43,708 --> 00:35:46,507
To make your play fun, it's okay to make mistakes.

906
00:35:46,508 --> 00:35:49,008
But you need to be confident.

907
00:35:49,778 --> 00:35:51,207
Just like Ju Eun said.

908
00:35:51,208 --> 00:35:53,547
Exactly! Just like Ju Eun said.

909
00:35:53,548 --> 00:35:55,478
I want you to be extra expressive.

910
00:35:55,688 --> 00:35:57,347
- Do you understand?
- Yes!

911
00:35:57,348 --> 00:35:58,447
Big movements!

912
00:35:58,448 --> 00:36:01,518
We're going to do it energetically from now on, okay?

913
00:36:01,988 --> 00:36:03,458
All right? Be energetic.

914
00:36:03,728 --> 00:36:05,087
Let's start over.

915
00:36:05,088 --> 00:36:06,698
All right, kids. You've got this.

916
00:36:06,998 --> 00:36:08,958
But I'm worried...

917
00:36:09,328 --> 00:36:10,928
Let's read it.

918
00:36:11,198 --> 00:36:14,168
When we randomly gave out the roles,

919
00:36:14,468 --> 00:36:17,238
they weren't embarrassed or anything.

920
00:36:17,408 --> 00:36:21,438
They only had fun while reading the script.

921
00:36:21,638 --> 00:36:24,447
Now, we're telling them, "This is the stage."

922
00:36:24,448 --> 00:36:27,118
"These are the outfits. These are your roles."

923
00:36:27,418 --> 00:36:29,547
I couldn't help but feel...

924
00:36:29,548 --> 00:36:32,918
that there's an invisible barrier.

925
00:36:33,318 --> 00:36:34,358
It's like...

926
00:36:37,528 --> 00:36:39,958
I think that's what people mean when they say...

927
00:36:41,198 --> 00:36:42,368
that you need experience.

928
00:36:42,868 --> 00:36:45,667
I keep having second thoughts...

929
00:36:45,668 --> 00:36:48,838
at the tiniest signals from the kids.

930
00:36:50,608 --> 00:36:52,677
And that's my fault for being inexperienced.

931
00:36:52,678 --> 00:36:54,978
(What if I were a better teacher?)

932
00:36:55,948 --> 00:36:57,778
Before class,

933
00:36:58,978 --> 00:37:00,477
I always thought,

934
00:37:00,478 --> 00:37:04,087
"They're going to love this. They'll want to..."

935
00:37:04,088 --> 00:37:07,018
"work harder when they see this."

936
00:37:07,558 --> 00:37:09,457
And they all go away...

937
00:37:09,458 --> 00:37:10,787
(Every time they go away)

938
00:37:10,788 --> 00:37:13,558
once the class starts.

939
00:37:14,198 --> 00:37:15,458
Every time that happened,

940
00:37:17,298 --> 00:37:18,667
I vaguely hoped...

941
00:37:18,668 --> 00:37:20,397
(She vaguely hoped they'd feel her sincerity.)

942
00:37:20,398 --> 00:37:24,168
that they would feel my sincerity.

943
00:37:29,448 --> 00:37:31,678
The kids will probably feel your sincerity, right?

944
00:37:34,118 --> 00:37:35,748
Kids won't know that.

945
00:37:37,018 --> 00:37:39,918
It's their first time performing a play.

946
00:37:53,538 --> 00:37:56,938
All of us are working this hard for just these seven kids.

947
00:37:57,708 --> 00:38:00,408
Just so they can experience what a play is...

948
00:38:01,208 --> 00:38:03,478
and so we can give them a chance...

949
00:38:03,808 --> 00:38:07,018
to see a new world.

950
00:38:09,318 --> 00:38:13,018
(They prepared for their classes with the kids every night.)

951
00:38:14,658 --> 00:38:16,628
- The Lion has done it!
- The Lion has done it!

952
00:38:17,458 --> 00:38:20,828
I believe I'll remember these moments for a long time.

953
00:38:21,258 --> 00:38:22,727
These moments pass, you know.

954
00:38:22,728 --> 00:38:24,068
(The time they spend together)

955
00:38:24,168 --> 00:38:28,437
These moments could be memorable events...

956
00:38:28,438 --> 00:38:29,837
(It could be a memorable moment for the children.)

957
00:38:29,838 --> 00:38:32,108
for every one of them, so they're meaningful.

958
00:38:32,508 --> 00:38:33,978
I think that's why...

959
00:38:35,238 --> 00:38:37,007
I get so ambitious.

960
00:38:37,008 --> 00:38:38,648
(Tae Ri gets ambitious.)

961
00:38:39,978 --> 00:38:42,348
(In fact...)

962
00:38:43,718 --> 00:38:45,087
(June)

963
00:38:45,088 --> 00:38:48,458
(Four months before coming to Mungyeong...)

964
00:38:48,888 --> 00:38:50,357
(Lee Si Hun)

965
00:38:50,358 --> 00:38:52,727
(She had asked the people around her for advice.)

966
00:38:52,728 --> 00:38:56,797
(Son Sang Gyu, actor and director)

967
00:38:56,798 --> 00:38:57,927
(Hye Ran)

968
00:38:57,928 --> 00:39:02,237
(She gave her all to this acting class.)

969
00:39:02,238 --> 00:39:03,438
Let's think.

970
00:39:05,568 --> 00:39:07,278
Who should I call?

971
00:39:07,708 --> 00:39:08,808
Let's try them all.

972
00:39:10,008 --> 00:39:11,177
(When she was lost)

973
00:39:11,178 --> 00:39:12,178
Hi!

974
00:39:12,618 --> 00:39:13,678
Hi.

975
00:39:14,318 --> 00:39:15,518
It's Tae Ri.

976
00:39:17,148 --> 00:39:20,587
I'm finally in an emergency.

977
00:39:20,588 --> 00:39:22,118
Actually,

978
00:39:23,288 --> 00:39:25,688
there have been about 85 emergencies.

979
00:39:26,198 --> 00:39:29,728
I wasn't sure what to talk about with them.

980
00:39:30,028 --> 00:39:32,267
I wanted your advice.

981
00:39:32,268 --> 00:39:33,498
(She sincerely asked for their advice.)

982
00:39:34,698 --> 00:39:36,438
Yes, good evening.

983
00:39:38,608 --> 00:39:39,608
(She mustered up her courage to make this phone call.)

984
00:39:39,609 --> 00:39:41,908
Hi, I'm Kim Tae Ri.

985
00:39:42,708 --> 00:39:45,878
This is my first time being a teacher,

986
00:39:46,078 --> 00:39:49,748
and it's my first time directing a play.

987
00:39:49,888 --> 00:39:51,987
I'm not exactly sure...

988
00:39:51,988 --> 00:39:54,117
what I should do...

989
00:39:54,118 --> 00:39:57,687
to lead them and help them open up.

990
00:39:57,688 --> 00:39:59,698
I have zero experience in this.

991
00:40:01,998 --> 00:40:03,827
I genuinely admire you.

992
00:40:03,828 --> 00:40:05,868
(And her notebook was packed with notes.)

993
00:40:07,798 --> 00:40:09,307
(What I'm missing about the children during class)

994
00:40:09,308 --> 00:40:10,707
(This isn't an evaluation. Keep them interested.)

995
00:40:10,708 --> 00:40:12,507
(No one falls behind! Don't scold them during breaks.)

996
00:40:12,508 --> 00:40:13,537
(Keep it free and fun!)

997
00:40:13,538 --> 00:40:16,747
(Everyone is the main character.)

998
00:40:16,748 --> 00:40:20,677
(The more she cared, the more she wanted to achieve out of love.)

999
00:40:20,678 --> 00:40:21,678
I don't...

1000
00:40:22,318 --> 00:40:25,548
want this to be remembered...

1001
00:40:26,118 --> 00:40:30,088
simply as putting on a play with them through hard work.

1002
00:40:35,158 --> 00:40:36,497
I wonder what they think.

1003
00:40:36,498 --> 00:40:37,668
(I wonder what they think about the acting class.)

1004
00:40:38,668 --> 00:40:40,437
Were they thinking at all?

1005
00:40:40,438 --> 00:40:43,008
(How do the children feel?)

1006
00:40:44,168 --> 00:40:47,477
(How long are we doing this?)

1007
00:40:47,478 --> 00:40:51,478
Kyung Mo wrote, "How long are we doing this?"

1008
00:40:56,818 --> 00:40:58,348
That hit hard.

1009
00:40:59,318 --> 00:41:00,558
It did.

1010
00:41:02,558 --> 00:41:05,157
But he's only in second grade, so it's understandable.

1011
00:41:05,158 --> 00:41:06,557
I just move on,

1012
00:41:06,558 --> 00:41:08,727
thinking it's understandable for a second-grader.

1013
00:41:08,728 --> 00:41:10,028
I just laughed it off.

1014
00:41:12,668 --> 00:41:14,638
What if that wasn't...

1015
00:41:15,798 --> 00:41:17,808
what Kyung Mo meant?

1016
00:41:18,308 --> 00:41:19,578
What? What could it have meant?

1017
00:41:22,008 --> 00:41:26,018
Can I ask you what you wrote in yesterday's question notes?

1018
00:41:26,978 --> 00:41:28,718
A sad thought.

1019
00:41:29,788 --> 00:41:31,748
What kind of sad thought?

1020
00:41:32,348 --> 00:41:35,588
The thought of the teachers leaving.

1021
00:41:38,788 --> 00:41:41,527
(How long are we doing this?)

1022
00:41:41,528 --> 00:41:43,727
(The teachers understood...)

1023
00:41:43,728 --> 00:41:46,968
(the exact opposite of what the kids meant.)

1024
00:41:48,868 --> 00:41:49,968
Camera.

1025
00:41:50,468 --> 00:41:52,038
Let's go home.

1026
00:41:57,048 --> 00:42:00,778
(One day after class)

1027
00:42:01,748 --> 00:42:03,748
Can the teachers stay?

1028
00:42:03,948 --> 00:42:04,988
Today?

1029
00:42:05,188 --> 00:42:07,188
- Can they stay?
- Forever?

1030
00:42:07,758 --> 00:42:10,257
Why do you want them to stay?

1031
00:42:10,258 --> 00:42:14,058
(The children opened up their hearts.)

1032
00:42:14,358 --> 00:42:16,298
- When they go home...
- Yes.

1033
00:42:16,698 --> 00:42:18,797
and the teachers aren't here,

1034
00:42:18,798 --> 00:42:19,798
Yes.

1035
00:42:20,238 --> 00:42:21,268
I feel...

1036
00:42:22,298 --> 00:42:23,768
a bit lonely.

1037
00:42:24,408 --> 00:42:27,578
Do you want the acting class to go on forever?

1038
00:42:27,678 --> 00:42:29,548
(Yes!)

1039
00:42:31,478 --> 00:42:33,748
I like the teachers.

1040
00:42:33,848 --> 00:42:34,878
Yes.

1041
00:42:34,978 --> 00:42:37,388
And the play is fun.

1042
00:42:40,618 --> 00:42:42,458
Why did you cry, Kyung Mo?

1043
00:42:43,728 --> 00:42:44,988
- Me?
- Yes.

1044
00:42:46,758 --> 00:42:50,827
I cried because I didn't want to say goodbye to the teachers.

1045
00:42:50,828 --> 00:42:53,098
(I cried because I didn't want to say goodbye to the teachers.)

1046
00:42:58,268 --> 00:42:59,268
(I don't want them to leave.)

1047
00:42:59,269 --> 00:43:00,507
(Please don't go!)

1048
00:43:00,508 --> 00:43:03,147
(Let's read the script together tomorrow!)

1049
00:43:03,148 --> 00:43:09,888
(The children also gave their all to the acting class.)

1050
00:43:10,118 --> 00:43:11,118
See you.

1051
00:43:11,119 --> 00:43:12,287
(After the fifth class)

1052
00:43:12,288 --> 00:43:13,318
Let's go!

1053
00:43:14,818 --> 00:43:16,888
We're going to create a group chatroom...

1054
00:43:17,088 --> 00:43:18,388
for practicing.

1055
00:43:19,228 --> 00:43:21,327
- Why?
- Can I make a group chatroom?

1056
00:43:21,328 --> 00:43:22,397
- Yes.
- Do you agree?

1057
00:43:22,398 --> 00:43:23,567
- No.
- I agree.

1058
00:43:23,568 --> 00:43:25,227
(The group chatroom they created)

1059
00:43:25,228 --> 00:43:26,737
(- I miss the teachers. - Me too.)

1060
00:43:26,738 --> 00:43:28,267
(- Who wants to read the script? - Can you practice?)

1061
00:43:28,268 --> 00:43:29,907
(- Do you want to? - I'll start the call.)

1062
00:43:29,908 --> 00:43:33,577
(Ha Yun, Hyo Min, Ju Eun, Do Hyun, and Kyung Mo)

1063
00:43:33,578 --> 00:43:37,278
(Even after class, they went home and...)

1064
00:43:37,478 --> 00:43:39,978
"Dorothy, we finally meet!"

1065
00:43:40,078 --> 00:43:43,318
"I knew you were going to meet the Wizard of Oz!"

1066
00:43:43,418 --> 00:43:45,748
(exchanged lines over the phone.)

1067
00:43:46,188 --> 00:43:48,687
"I'll get going now. Bye, everyone."

1068
00:43:48,688 --> 00:43:49,688
(Every night, they prepared to meet their teachers.)

1069
00:43:49,689 --> 00:43:50,957
Okay, the end!

1070
00:43:50,958 --> 00:43:52,758
We're done. I'll leave the call.

1071
00:43:53,358 --> 00:43:55,127
- Okay.
- No, you can't.

1072
00:43:55,128 --> 00:43:56,768
We have to practice together.

1073
00:43:56,868 --> 00:43:59,298
Acting classes are ending soon. How do you feel?

1074
00:44:03,268 --> 00:44:05,038
I'm a little sad.

1075
00:44:05,538 --> 00:44:06,678
Are you sad?

1076
00:44:09,238 --> 00:44:11,347
Aren't you going to tell the teachers how you feel?

1077
00:44:11,348 --> 00:44:13,448
- No.
- Why not?

1078
00:44:13,648 --> 00:44:17,288
Because it might make them sad.

1079
00:44:17,448 --> 00:44:19,558
- Is that why you won't tell them?
- Yes.

1080
00:44:23,058 --> 00:44:25,087
Today is the seventh class, right?

1081
00:44:25,088 --> 00:44:26,798
The seventh. How many more do we have left?

1082
00:44:27,398 --> 00:44:30,168
Next week, we'll have to say bye. I mean it.

1083
00:44:31,468 --> 00:44:33,168
Let's try it.

1084
00:44:33,268 --> 00:44:34,867
Let's try to work on it together.

1085
00:44:34,868 --> 00:44:38,107
Let's have fun and do our best to make it work. Okay?

1086
00:44:38,108 --> 00:44:40,038
- Okay.
- Yes. Let's try it.

1087
00:44:40,138 --> 00:44:41,178
Let's try it.

1088
00:44:48,318 --> 00:44:52,288
(Ha Yun held back his tears.)

1089
00:44:56,328 --> 00:44:59,697
(The children are clumsy with expressing themselves,)

1090
00:44:59,698 --> 00:45:03,768
(and the adults are clumsy with being patient.)

1091
00:45:07,738 --> 00:45:13,738
(Time passed by without being able to share their sincerity.)

1092
00:45:18,109 --> 00:45:19,408
(Meanwhile, North Pole Teacher is busy.)

1093
00:45:19,409 --> 00:45:20,709
They'll like this, right?

1094
00:45:22,379 --> 00:45:24,508
Time is almost running out.

1095
00:45:24,509 --> 00:45:26,479
Can I call it our final memory?

1096
00:45:26,879 --> 00:45:29,119
It's a means to get even closer with the kids.

1097
00:45:29,219 --> 00:45:31,219
We'll have fun in the garden with everyone.

1098
00:45:31,719 --> 00:45:33,318
Here I go. Heave-ho.

1099
00:45:33,319 --> 00:45:36,958
We bought a lot of food. We'll cook for them.

1100
00:45:36,959 --> 00:45:38,358
(Today's helpers)

1101
00:45:38,359 --> 00:45:39,859
Some soy sauce.

1102
00:45:40,799 --> 00:45:42,029
This pot is really nice.

1103
00:45:42,429 --> 00:45:45,429
What a stylish color. It's nice.

1104
00:45:45,769 --> 00:45:47,339
I'll boil a lot.

1105
00:45:48,439 --> 00:45:51,238
(Grilling some chubby sausages)

1106
00:45:51,239 --> 00:45:52,869
This frying pan is really pretty.

1107
00:45:57,179 --> 00:45:58,249
What do I do?

1108
00:45:59,179 --> 00:46:00,449
This one fell on the ground.

1109
00:46:01,549 --> 00:46:02,619
I have no other choice.

1110
00:46:03,919 --> 00:46:04,949
It fell.

1111
00:46:05,519 --> 00:46:08,089
(Is it going in the pot because he dropped it?)

1112
00:46:08,859 --> 00:46:10,358
I'm too hungry.

1113
00:46:10,359 --> 00:46:12,189
(Sanitizing it in boiling water)

1114
00:46:12,829 --> 00:46:14,899
I don't think I'll have the chance to eat later.

1115
00:46:15,659 --> 00:46:16,829
I'd better eat.

1116
00:46:17,329 --> 00:46:20,139
(He has no choice but to have some ramyeon.)

1117
00:46:26,679 --> 00:46:29,709
(Eating the sausage he had no choice but to boil)

1118
00:46:31,679 --> 00:46:35,348
(He has no choice but to check if the fish cakes are cooked.)

1119
00:46:35,349 --> 00:46:36,489
Gosh, that is amazing.

1120
00:46:37,849 --> 00:46:39,618
It's so delicious. I could sell it.

1121
00:46:39,619 --> 00:46:41,819
(Thanks to that, the dishes are deliciously ready.)

1122
00:46:43,259 --> 00:46:44,259
There we go.

1123
00:46:44,260 --> 00:46:45,729
(Moving the completed dishes)

1124
00:46:47,529 --> 00:46:49,228
Will it catch on fire if I do this?

1125
00:46:49,229 --> 00:46:50,229
(Starting a fire)

1126
00:46:51,429 --> 00:46:52,429
There it is.

1127
00:46:52,430 --> 00:46:53,768
(He finished preparing for camping.)

1128
00:46:53,769 --> 00:46:56,338
Sniff, sniff, I can smell fire!

1129
00:46:56,339 --> 00:46:57,938
It smells like fire!

1130
00:46:57,939 --> 00:46:59,939
All my straws might burn away!

1131
00:47:01,139 --> 00:47:03,309
(The acting class of Oz is here.)

1132
00:47:03,979 --> 00:47:06,278
It's Potato Teacher!

1133
00:47:06,279 --> 00:47:08,648
It's the handsome North Pole Teacher!

1134
00:47:08,649 --> 00:47:10,789
All right, gather around.

1135
00:47:10,889 --> 00:47:11,988
(The camping starts.)

1136
00:47:11,989 --> 00:47:13,889
Be careful of the fire.

1137
00:47:14,689 --> 00:47:15,889
Who's hungry?

1138
00:47:15,989 --> 00:47:17,188
- Me!
- Me!

1139
00:47:17,189 --> 00:47:18,558
Please wait a bit.

1140
00:47:18,559 --> 00:47:20,598
Potato Teacher is barbecuing.

1141
00:47:20,599 --> 00:47:22,329
- Okay!
- Please wait.

1142
00:47:22,659 --> 00:47:24,298
It looks delicious!

1143
00:47:24,299 --> 00:47:26,329
(The sausages are covered in a smoky scent.)

1144
00:47:27,039 --> 00:47:28,239
It's not a dream, is it?

1145
00:47:29,339 --> 00:47:31,339
(Is this a dream?)

1146
00:47:31,539 --> 00:47:32,568
It's not a dream, is it?

1147
00:47:32,569 --> 00:47:35,238
It's real!

1148
00:47:35,239 --> 00:47:37,879
If you like camping, scream!

1149
00:47:38,079 --> 00:47:39,079
(Screaming)

1150
00:47:40,349 --> 00:47:43,289
If you like acting class, scream!

1151
00:47:43,689 --> 00:47:47,018
(Screaming!)

1152
00:47:47,019 --> 00:47:50,889
Gosh. They don't need us.

1153
00:47:50,989 --> 00:47:52,488
No. They're having fun all on their own.

1154
00:47:52,489 --> 00:47:54,329
(Meanwhile, the teachers are busy.)

1155
00:47:57,199 --> 00:47:59,229
- Please sit in the middle.
- Amazing!

1156
00:48:00,339 --> 00:48:02,298
It looks so good. Hey, there are fish cakes.

1157
00:48:02,299 --> 00:48:03,968
The fish cake looks so good!

1158
00:48:03,969 --> 00:48:05,069
There are fish cakes!

1159
00:48:08,009 --> 00:48:10,348
Now that I think about it, there is no kimchi.

1160
00:48:10,349 --> 00:48:11,478
- You're right.
- There is no kimchi!

1161
00:48:11,479 --> 00:48:12,909
There is no kimchi!

1162
00:48:13,679 --> 00:48:15,018
Can you eat kimchi?

1163
00:48:15,019 --> 00:48:16,019
- Yes!
- Yes!

1164
00:48:16,020 --> 00:48:17,718
Koreans must eat kimchi!

1165
00:48:17,719 --> 00:48:19,888
They think we're babies.

1166
00:48:19,889 --> 00:48:20,889
Are you serious?

1167
00:48:20,890 --> 00:48:22,259
- Yes.
- Of course.

1168
00:48:22,359 --> 00:48:23,529
Are you all grown-ups?

1169
00:48:24,959 --> 00:48:27,159
Teacher, can we start eating?

1170
00:48:27,599 --> 00:48:28,829
I'm hungry.

1171
00:48:29,059 --> 00:48:30,368
I'll eat after the adults eat.

1172
00:48:30,369 --> 00:48:31,769
I will too.

1173
00:48:31,869 --> 00:48:34,339
I will eat only after the adults start.

1174
00:48:36,239 --> 00:48:38,469
(Getting a little taste)

1175
00:48:38,609 --> 00:48:42,209
Teachers! Can you taste one?

1176
00:48:42,839 --> 00:48:44,549
- Please.
- Okay.

1177
00:48:44,779 --> 00:48:45,979
Okay, I'll eat one.

1178
00:48:46,279 --> 00:48:48,178
- Okay!
- Okay!

1179
00:48:48,179 --> 00:48:49,579
(They are able to respect their elders.)

1180
00:48:49,679 --> 00:48:51,549
I'm so full! I mean, I'm so hungry!

1181
00:48:51,649 --> 00:48:53,889
- Thank you for the food!
- Thank you for the food!

1182
00:48:53,989 --> 00:48:55,959
Thank you for the food. Enjoy.

1183
00:48:56,359 --> 00:48:58,729
(Biting)

1184
00:48:59,089 --> 00:49:00,698
(Eating)

1185
00:49:00,699 --> 00:49:01,899
In one bite.

1186
00:49:02,299 --> 00:49:03,299
(Delicious)

1187
00:49:03,769 --> 00:49:06,598
Gosh. This must be the taste of camping.

1188
00:49:06,599 --> 00:49:08,799
(Enjoying the taste of camping)

1189
00:49:09,439 --> 00:49:10,738
Can I have a fish cake?

1190
00:49:10,739 --> 00:49:13,039
Of course. It's all for you guys.

1191
00:49:14,379 --> 00:49:17,478
(Kyung Mo is eating a fish cake.)

1192
00:49:17,479 --> 00:49:19,549
(Slurping)

1193
00:49:20,879 --> 00:49:22,418
(One fish cake for Potato)

1194
00:49:22,419 --> 00:49:23,689
This is too big.

1195
00:49:25,149 --> 00:49:27,458
(Now he's going on the meat after having fish cake.)

1196
00:49:27,459 --> 00:49:29,089
Kyung Mo is eating so well.

1197
00:49:29,189 --> 00:49:31,389
Kyung Mo is eating so well.

1198
00:49:31,589 --> 00:49:32,788
You're eating so well.

1199
00:49:32,789 --> 00:49:34,328
- Why did you stop?
- Kyung Mo...

1200
00:49:34,329 --> 00:49:35,998
- You should have left him alone.
- Keep eating.

1201
00:49:35,999 --> 00:49:37,768
- Keep eating.
- What is it?

1202
00:49:37,769 --> 00:49:39,129
(Frozen because of the sudden attention)

1203
00:49:40,339 --> 00:49:41,339
(Meanwhile, Won Jin...)

1204
00:49:41,340 --> 00:49:43,769
- It's delicious.
- Please give me more kimchi.

1205
00:49:45,639 --> 00:49:48,679
(His frown sincerely expresses the taste.)

1206
00:49:49,739 --> 00:49:52,749
(Big bite of a sausage)

1207
00:49:52,909 --> 00:49:53,919
- This hurts.
- Delicious.

1208
00:49:54,379 --> 00:49:55,479
Do you want more kimchi?

1209
00:49:55,679 --> 00:49:58,719
(He's good at eating kimchi too.)

1210
00:49:58,819 --> 00:50:01,118
When we said, "Cheers,"

1211
00:50:01,119 --> 00:50:04,058
you looked at me like this.

1212
00:50:04,059 --> 00:50:05,258
(The baby lion's chopsticks are running wild.)

1213
00:50:05,259 --> 00:50:07,829
Where do you do it like this?

1214
00:50:08,499 --> 00:50:10,029
When we gather at 6:00pm...

1215
00:50:12,499 --> 00:50:13,539
Did you finish already?

1216
00:50:13,939 --> 00:50:16,469
North Pole Teacher, can I have some more?

1217
00:50:16,569 --> 00:50:17,769
- What do you want?
- Won Jin, are you having more?

1218
00:50:18,239 --> 00:50:19,669
Rice? What do you want?

1219
00:50:19,939 --> 00:50:22,508
- We're out of rice.
- If you scrape this together,

1220
00:50:22,509 --> 00:50:25,209
you will get a fistful at least.

1221
00:50:25,549 --> 00:50:26,549
Here.

1222
00:50:27,019 --> 00:50:28,649
That's all we have. Do you want sausages?

1223
00:50:29,479 --> 00:50:31,088
- Is it good?
- Yes.

1224
00:50:31,089 --> 00:50:32,619
(Satisfied)

1225
00:50:33,619 --> 00:50:35,788
(Now that they're full...)

1226
00:50:35,789 --> 00:50:37,989
Here, have a drink.

1227
00:50:38,559 --> 00:50:41,329
Let's toast with our water. Cheers!

1228
00:50:41,559 --> 00:50:42,858
Let's be excited. Cheers!

1229
00:50:42,859 --> 00:50:44,768
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

1230
00:50:44,769 --> 00:50:46,799
(It's a tasty time thanks to being together.)

1231
00:50:48,299 --> 00:50:51,039
- Guys!
- Yes?

1232
00:50:51,139 --> 00:50:53,338
Today, we're camping.

1233
00:50:53,339 --> 00:50:57,049
This is the last time we can meet outside of class...

1234
00:50:57,549 --> 00:51:01,519
before our big performance.

1235
00:51:02,419 --> 00:51:07,018
Okay? That is why the teachers worked hard to prepare this.

1236
00:51:07,019 --> 00:51:09,158
I hope you enjoy the food.

1237
00:51:09,159 --> 00:51:11,488
It's our last chance to hang out together.

1238
00:51:11,489 --> 00:51:12,489
Yes.

1239
00:51:12,689 --> 00:51:14,499
(They're suddenly quiet.)

1240
00:51:15,699 --> 00:51:16,869
We should have told you after eating.

1241
00:51:18,369 --> 00:51:19,428
That was bad timing.

1242
00:51:19,429 --> 00:51:20,968
(They are solemn.)

1243
00:51:20,969 --> 00:51:22,538
No, please enjoy the food.

1244
00:51:22,539 --> 00:51:23,968
- Okay?
- Enjoy the food.

1245
00:51:23,969 --> 00:51:24,969
Enjoy.

1246
00:51:24,970 --> 00:51:26,638
(Okay)

1247
00:51:26,639 --> 00:51:28,209
Look at me, teachers.

1248
00:51:28,309 --> 00:51:30,379
(Eating kimchi)

1249
00:51:30,649 --> 00:51:32,049
I didn't know you could eat kimchi.

1250
00:51:32,879 --> 00:51:35,118
Do you think we're babies?

1251
00:51:35,119 --> 00:51:36,889
I only started eating kimchi after I went to middle school.

1252
00:51:37,119 --> 00:51:38,119
- Middle school.
- Are you weak at spiciness?

1253
00:51:38,649 --> 00:51:40,118
I couldn't eat it at first because it was too spicy.

1254
00:51:40,119 --> 00:51:41,418
(Won Jin mastered it long ago.)

1255
00:51:41,419 --> 00:51:43,218
- At 9am?
- My bus comes at 10am.

1256
00:51:43,219 --> 00:51:44,788
- And at 8am...
- After finishing this meal...

1257
00:51:44,789 --> 00:51:45,988
He looks like a CEO.

1258
00:51:45,989 --> 00:51:47,159
Exactly. Right?

1259
00:51:48,799 --> 00:51:51,328
(Serious)

1260
00:51:51,329 --> 00:51:53,099
What do you do on your day off?

1261
00:51:53,799 --> 00:51:55,668
- Go downtown.
- With your friends?

1262
00:51:55,669 --> 00:51:56,768
- Yes.
- We go out to play!

1263
00:51:56,769 --> 00:51:58,509
Together? What do you do at the downtown?

1264
00:51:59,409 --> 00:52:00,779
What do you do, Mr. CEO?

1265
00:52:01,339 --> 00:52:02,478
I don't go downtown.

1266
00:52:02,479 --> 00:52:03,479
No?

1267
00:52:04,379 --> 00:52:05,449
Mr. CEO.

1268
00:52:06,309 --> 00:52:07,918
It's CEO Jang.

1269
00:52:07,919 --> 00:52:09,618
- CEO Jang.
- CEO Jang.

1270
00:52:09,619 --> 00:52:12,689
Your posture is charismatic, CEO Jang.

1271
00:52:13,019 --> 00:52:14,889
Why are you wearing your outfit so warmly?

1272
00:52:14,989 --> 00:52:16,719
CEO Jang, what is your dream?

1273
00:52:17,289 --> 00:52:19,828
- A policeman.
- A policeman? Really?

1274
00:52:19,829 --> 00:52:21,699
Let's go around and share our dreams.

1275
00:52:21,799 --> 00:52:23,898
- Okay.
- Let's talk about dreams.

1276
00:52:23,899 --> 00:52:25,628
Let's start with Kyung Mo.

1277
00:52:25,629 --> 00:52:27,769
Okay. Kyung Mo! What is your dream, Kyung Mo?

1278
00:52:27,869 --> 00:52:28,899
- Me?
- Yes.

1279
00:52:29,139 --> 00:52:30,438
- As for me...
- Yes?

1280
00:52:30,439 --> 00:52:31,708
It changes every day, but...

1281
00:52:31,709 --> 00:52:32,769
- Okay.
- What is it today?

1282
00:52:33,369 --> 00:52:35,678
It was a boxer, but now it's a runner.

1283
00:52:35,679 --> 00:52:37,178
A runner.

1284
00:52:37,179 --> 00:52:38,208
A runner?

1285
00:52:38,209 --> 00:52:39,779
- What about Hyo Min?
- What's your dream, Hyo Min?

1286
00:52:40,449 --> 00:52:42,319
An actor is one of them.

1287
00:52:42,919 --> 00:52:44,148
- Really?
- What?

1288
00:52:44,149 --> 00:52:46,119
- An actor is one of them.
- An actor.

1289
00:52:46,489 --> 00:52:49,088
- Did the classes inspire you?
- Yes.

1290
00:52:49,089 --> 00:52:50,488
(The children have new dreams.)

1291
00:52:50,489 --> 00:52:52,059
Was it that fun?

1292
00:52:54,759 --> 00:52:58,499
(The first day of Ms. Kim's post)

1293
00:52:59,369 --> 00:53:02,099
This student's dream is to become a webtoon artist!

1294
00:53:03,139 --> 00:53:05,038
"Won Jin, my dear self whom I love,"

1295
00:53:05,039 --> 00:53:06,369
"let's become a policeman when I grow up."

1296
00:53:06,639 --> 00:53:10,709
(Their dreams could be found around the classroom.)

1297
00:53:12,909 --> 00:53:15,319
What is your dream now, Hyo Min?

1298
00:53:15,949 --> 00:53:19,289
I haven't decided yet, but I only have three.

1299
00:53:19,549 --> 00:53:20,959
What are the three?

1300
00:53:21,259 --> 00:53:24,389
Flight attendant, actor, and baseball player.

1301
00:53:25,159 --> 00:53:28,098
Did you want to become an actor after the acting classes?

1302
00:53:28,099 --> 00:53:29,159
Yes.

1303
00:53:31,369 --> 00:53:34,839
I still want to be a runner.

1304
00:53:37,739 --> 00:53:40,509
But I want to do plays.

1305
00:53:41,279 --> 00:53:44,378
I want to become a baseball player or a basketball player,

1306
00:53:44,379 --> 00:53:48,079
but I've started to want to become a theater actor too.

1307
00:53:50,419 --> 00:53:54,819
(They were newly introduced to the world of theater.)

1308
00:53:55,389 --> 00:53:57,228
Do you have any marshmallows?

1309
00:53:57,229 --> 00:53:59,128
- I like it.
- Marshmallows?

1310
00:53:59,129 --> 00:54:00,798
Do we have any, teachers?

1311
00:54:00,799 --> 00:54:02,929
- We have some, don't we?
- Marshmallows?

1312
00:54:04,669 --> 00:54:06,429
Hey, they have marshmallows!

1313
00:54:07,069 --> 00:54:08,439
Marshmallows.

1314
00:54:09,499 --> 00:54:11,108
(Marshmallow)

1315
00:54:11,109 --> 00:54:12,909
(Marshmallow)

1316
00:54:13,269 --> 00:54:15,738
(CEO Jang is excited.)

1317
00:54:15,739 --> 00:54:17,549
- Have you roasted one before?
- Yes.

1318
00:54:18,279 --> 00:54:19,378
Do you want to stick them on?

1319
00:54:19,379 --> 00:54:21,049
- Yes!
- Yes!

1320
00:54:21,419 --> 00:54:22,878
Be careful of the fire.

1321
00:54:22,879 --> 00:54:24,788
(A marshmallow party has started.)

1322
00:54:24,789 --> 00:54:26,118
Ms. Kim, I'll roast one nicely for you.

1323
00:54:26,119 --> 00:54:27,919
You sound like a marshmallow expert.

1324
00:54:29,759 --> 00:54:32,029
- Was it refreshing?
- Yes.

1325
00:54:32,989 --> 00:54:34,128
Teacher.

1326
00:54:34,129 --> 00:54:35,829
(Serious)

1327
00:54:36,969 --> 00:54:38,229
Did I roast it well?

1328
00:54:39,229 --> 00:54:40,538
You did really well.

1329
00:54:40,539 --> 00:54:41,869
(They make us drool.)

1330
00:54:42,169 --> 00:54:43,198
(Crispy)

1331
00:54:43,199 --> 00:54:44,708
Do you eat it right away? That looks so good.

1332
00:54:44,709 --> 00:54:45,709
(The taste has her eyes wide.)

1333
00:54:45,710 --> 00:54:46,809
Is it good?

1334
00:54:47,009 --> 00:54:48,979
- It's really good.
- She says it's good.

1335
00:54:49,539 --> 00:54:51,509
Wicked Witch of the West is good at roasting!

1336
00:54:51,779 --> 00:54:53,448
She can control the fire.

1337
00:54:53,449 --> 00:54:55,979
Wicked Witch of the West is really good...

1338
00:54:56,519 --> 00:54:57,849
at roasting marshmallows.

1339
00:54:58,219 --> 00:54:59,489
The Wicked Witch of the West?

1340
00:55:00,019 --> 00:55:01,089
Ju Eun?

1341
00:55:01,489 --> 00:55:02,618
Is Ju Eun good at roasting?

1342
00:55:02,619 --> 00:55:03,628
(Naturally getting a refill)

1343
00:55:03,629 --> 00:55:06,089
- Is it good?
- Please give me another one.

1344
00:55:06,629 --> 00:55:07,729
One more?

1345
00:55:07,859 --> 00:55:09,428
Look, I roasted one for you.

1346
00:55:09,429 --> 00:55:10,798
Ha Yun.

1347
00:55:10,799 --> 00:55:13,098
- Thank you.
- It's a little burnt.

1348
00:55:13,099 --> 00:55:14,639
It's okay. I'm good at eating burnt food.

1349
00:55:15,139 --> 00:55:16,698
Peel it off and eat it.

1350
00:55:16,699 --> 00:55:18,038
- What?
- Peel it off.

1351
00:55:18,039 --> 00:55:19,569
- Thank you.
- Sure.

1352
00:55:20,039 --> 00:55:22,478
I haven't had it in a while, so it tastes really good.

1353
00:55:22,479 --> 00:55:24,208
- Hurray!
- You have to pull it off.

1354
00:55:24,209 --> 00:55:25,349
How do you do that?

1355
00:55:25,849 --> 00:55:27,578
Pull it up.

1356
00:55:27,579 --> 00:55:29,978
- I'll roast a mushroom for you.
- Give me one more.

1357
00:55:29,979 --> 00:55:31,419
Eat just that piece.

1358
00:55:31,819 --> 00:55:33,488
- Just this?
- It's really good.

1359
00:55:33,489 --> 00:55:34,759
(Going in)

1360
00:55:34,889 --> 00:55:36,019
It's so good.

1361
00:55:36,259 --> 00:55:38,229
It's delicious. Thank you, Ju Eun.

1362
00:55:40,029 --> 00:55:41,458
- Ta-da.
- Go ahead and eat it.

1363
00:55:41,459 --> 00:55:43,329
- It's delicious. Have them both.
- Is it good?

1364
00:55:45,069 --> 00:55:46,928
- It's so good.
- Look at this!

1365
00:55:46,929 --> 00:55:47,938
(Everyone is gifting marshmallows.)

1366
00:55:47,939 --> 00:55:49,599
- It's nicely roasted.
- It's nicely roasted.

1367
00:55:50,369 --> 00:55:53,709
(Meanwhile, someone is having a party of her own.)

1368
00:55:53,909 --> 00:55:56,139
Dorothy likes marshmallows.

1369
00:55:56,239 --> 00:55:57,979
- Dorothy?
- Here.

1370
00:55:58,109 --> 00:55:59,578
(Eating)

1371
00:55:59,579 --> 00:56:01,618
(Eating again)

1372
00:56:01,619 --> 00:56:02,719
(And eating some more)

1373
00:56:03,079 --> 00:56:04,119
Isn't it good?

1374
00:56:04,649 --> 00:56:05,719
You really like this, don't you?

1375
00:56:07,419 --> 00:56:08,658
Eun Soo is devouring it.

1376
00:56:08,659 --> 00:56:09,819
(So cute)

1377
00:56:10,019 --> 00:56:12,289
How many did you have, Eun Soo?

1378
00:56:13,489 --> 00:56:14,899
Did you have more than six?

1379
00:56:15,599 --> 00:56:17,329
- Yes.
- More than six?

1380
00:56:18,429 --> 00:56:21,269
I think you'd better stop.

1381
00:56:21,599 --> 00:56:23,538
- You should stop.
- You'd better stop.

1382
00:56:23,539 --> 00:56:24,869
(Finishing her last piece)

1383
00:56:25,309 --> 00:56:28,439
Potato Teacher, we'll stop roasting marshmallows!

1384
00:56:28,609 --> 00:56:30,238
Okay, stop eating!

1385
00:56:30,239 --> 00:56:31,248
(End of the marshmallow party)

1386
00:56:31,249 --> 00:56:32,409
You had too much.

1387
00:56:32,849 --> 00:56:33,878
Okay, guys.

1388
00:56:33,879 --> 00:56:35,448
Look at what North Pole Teacher is holding.

1389
00:56:35,449 --> 00:56:37,249
- What is that?
- Doesn't it turn on?

1390
00:56:37,889 --> 00:56:41,219
It's when we think of our parents at home, right?

1391
00:56:41,489 --> 00:56:44,728
Yes. Whenever we teachers...

1392
00:56:44,729 --> 00:56:47,928
went on retreats or field trips,

1393
00:56:47,929 --> 00:56:50,469
- we used candles.
- I think I might cry doing it.

1394
00:56:50,569 --> 00:56:53,968
We don't have much time left,

1395
00:56:53,969 --> 00:56:56,198
but we already spent a lot of time together.

1396
00:56:56,199 --> 00:56:58,268
It has been almost two weeks.

1397
00:56:58,269 --> 00:57:01,139
So why don't we share how it was for the last two weeks?

1398
00:57:01,939 --> 00:57:02,939
How was it?

1399
00:57:02,940 --> 00:57:04,648
What was it like when you first met us?

1400
00:57:04,649 --> 00:57:06,108
When you met the teachers for the first time.

1401
00:57:06,109 --> 00:57:07,979
- You met Ms. Kim first, right?
- Yes.

1402
00:57:08,879 --> 00:57:10,079
In the very beginning,

1403
00:57:10,589 --> 00:57:13,618
someone shushed us and said, "It's starting."

1404
00:57:13,619 --> 00:57:14,619
Look.

1405
00:57:14,620 --> 00:57:15,789
What is this?

1406
00:57:16,319 --> 00:57:20,158
(Ms. Kim appeared and put on a 1-man play.)

1407
00:57:20,159 --> 00:57:21,528
I performed a play for you!

1408
00:57:21,529 --> 00:57:25,168
And then you suddenly went, "I like mountains."

1409
00:57:25,169 --> 00:57:27,638
You're right! You remember it all.

1410
00:57:27,639 --> 00:57:29,069
(They remember her motions too.)

1411
00:57:29,299 --> 00:57:32,168
Then Potato Teacher came out from behind the door.

1412
00:57:32,169 --> 00:57:33,979
- Hello.
- Hello!

1413
00:57:34,579 --> 00:57:35,938
(Potato Teacher was shy.)

1414
00:57:35,939 --> 00:57:40,179
- Hello.
- And then North Pole Teacher...

1415
00:57:40,279 --> 00:57:41,279
He was on a bicycle.

1416
00:57:41,280 --> 00:57:43,179
He trespassed.

1417
00:57:44,049 --> 00:57:45,688
Did he trespass?

1418
00:57:45,689 --> 00:57:46,948
(Trespasser North Pole Teacher)

1419
00:57:46,949 --> 00:57:48,188
- North Pole?
- North Pole.

1420
00:57:48,189 --> 00:57:49,658
That was a while ago.

1421
00:57:49,659 --> 00:57:52,828
We don't have so many days left now.

1422
00:57:52,829 --> 00:57:55,799
We spent two weeks together.

1423
00:57:56,159 --> 00:57:58,898
I'm sad that we have to leave in two days.

1424
00:57:58,899 --> 00:58:01,299
- Can't you stay longer?
- Please stay longer.

1425
00:58:02,039 --> 00:58:03,669
- What?
- Please stay longer.

1426
00:58:04,709 --> 00:58:06,039
I'm tearing up.

1427
00:58:06,139 --> 00:58:08,039
It's okay. You can cry.

1428
00:58:09,009 --> 00:58:10,809
- It's okay to cry.
- Why?

1429
00:58:11,149 --> 00:58:12,308
Just stay!

1430
00:58:12,309 --> 00:58:13,678
(Their parting is nearing.)

1431
00:58:13,679 --> 00:58:15,719
- Gosh, Eun Soo...
- Is Eun Soo crying?

1432
00:58:15,879 --> 00:58:17,389
Dorothy, are you crying? Why?

1433
00:58:17,489 --> 00:58:18,889
I'm so sad.

1434
00:58:19,819 --> 00:58:21,258
(Her sadness is in her eyes.)

1435
00:58:21,259 --> 00:58:22,289
What is it, Dorothy?

1436
00:58:22,559 --> 00:58:23,559
Gosh.

1437
00:58:28,099 --> 00:58:30,629
Do Hyun, why are you crying?

1438
00:58:33,129 --> 00:58:35,498
(The tears are contagious.)

1439
00:58:35,499 --> 00:58:37,269
Gosh.

1440
00:58:38,839 --> 00:58:40,039
- My goodness.
- Why?

1441
00:58:40,809 --> 00:58:42,539
I'm not gone yet.

1442
00:58:42,979 --> 00:58:45,179
They're sad because this is the last time.

1443
00:58:45,979 --> 00:58:47,918
Ms. Kim, they're sad because this is the last time.

1444
00:58:47,919 --> 00:58:49,379
- Sure...
- We'll leave soon.

1445
00:58:50,889 --> 00:58:53,649
I guess we grew more fond of each other than I thought.

1446
00:58:53,859 --> 00:58:54,919
Exactly.

1447
00:58:57,429 --> 00:59:01,059
(Their heart for each other corresponds to the time together.)

1448
00:59:04,169 --> 00:59:09,839
(The children are not used to saying goodbye.)

1449
00:59:11,469 --> 00:59:12,669
Gosh.

1450
00:59:13,339 --> 00:59:14,838
I don't know what to do.

1451
00:59:14,839 --> 00:59:16,079
(Ju Eun remains mature even in this situation.)

1452
00:59:17,039 --> 00:59:19,478
- Kyung Mo.
- Kyung Mo. Look at him.

1453
00:59:19,479 --> 00:59:22,618
- Hey, it's okay.
- Kyung Mo.

1454
00:59:22,619 --> 00:59:23,819
Hey.

1455
00:59:24,249 --> 00:59:25,249
Are you that sad?

1456
00:59:25,919 --> 00:59:26,919
Seriously?

1457
00:59:29,319 --> 00:59:31,658
I'm still here.

1458
00:59:31,659 --> 00:59:32,759
Hyo Min.

1459
00:59:33,429 --> 00:59:35,398
I've never seen Hyo Min cry like this.

1460
00:59:35,399 --> 00:59:36,629
(A rare sighting even for his best friend)

1461
00:59:36,729 --> 00:59:37,729
(No!)

1462
00:59:39,169 --> 00:59:41,299
Okay, enough. We got it.

1463
00:59:42,069 --> 00:59:43,938
Are you guys that sad?

1464
00:59:43,939 --> 00:59:45,468
(Suddenly, everyone is wailing.)

1465
00:59:45,469 --> 00:59:46,539
Come on.

1466
00:59:47,239 --> 00:59:50,808
(They never expected the kids to be so sad.)

1467
00:59:50,809 --> 00:59:53,049
Guys, what do we have to do to make you laugh?

1468
00:59:53,749 --> 00:59:55,719
Hey, let's talk about something fun now.

1469
00:59:56,149 --> 00:59:57,848
What was the funniest in the last two weeks?

1470
00:59:57,849 --> 01:00:00,989
Talking about that makes me cry even more.

1471
01:00:01,319 --> 01:00:03,759
- But it's about something fun.
- Stop talking!

1472
01:00:04,059 --> 01:00:06,159
- No.
- But it's about something fun.

1473
01:00:07,599 --> 01:00:08,658
Guys!

1474
01:00:08,659 --> 01:00:10,528
(They must try a countermeasure.)

1475
01:00:10,529 --> 01:00:11,529
Guys!

1476
01:00:11,669 --> 01:00:14,069
It must be the candles. Let's turn them off.

1477
01:00:14,639 --> 01:00:17,139
Hand them to me. It must be the candles.

1478
01:00:17,639 --> 01:00:18,809
Give me the candles.

1479
01:00:18,939 --> 01:00:20,838
Let's play a game of word chain.

1480
01:00:20,839 --> 01:00:22,079
Are you good at word chain?

1481
01:00:22,179 --> 01:00:23,308
Word chain.

1482
01:00:23,309 --> 01:00:25,579
(It's impossible to move on.)

1483
01:00:25,709 --> 01:00:27,849
Number game. I'm one!

1484
01:00:31,849 --> 01:00:34,558
(It has an adverse reaction.)

1485
01:00:34,559 --> 01:00:36,659
Okay, what do you want to eat? Tell me what you want to eat.

1486
01:00:36,859 --> 01:00:38,629
Apples! I want to eat apples.

1487
01:00:38,729 --> 01:00:39,928
I'll bring some apples!

1488
01:00:39,929 --> 01:00:42,298
(I'll bring some apples!)

1489
01:00:42,299 --> 01:00:45,069
- I've never seen Tae Ri so fast.
- Me neither.

1490
01:00:45,899 --> 01:00:48,099
Are they still crying? Still?

1491
01:00:48,469 --> 01:00:51,738
- It's the apple we picked together.
- An apple!

1492
01:00:51,739 --> 01:00:53,069
Mungyeong apple.

1493
01:00:53,909 --> 01:00:56,409
- Kyung Mo, let's eat it.
- Take it.

1494
01:00:56,909 --> 01:00:58,108
(He'll take an apple even while crying.)

1495
01:00:58,109 --> 01:01:02,178
All right, okay.

1496
01:01:02,179 --> 01:01:03,449
(It's no use.)

1497
01:01:05,349 --> 01:01:07,288
(Crunch)

1498
01:01:07,289 --> 01:01:09,288
Okay, everyone! Ready, go!

1499
01:01:09,289 --> 01:01:11,259
- One, two, three, four.
- One, two, three, four.

1500
01:01:11,529 --> 01:01:12,589
(Crying)

1501
01:01:13,159 --> 01:01:16,228
(Failing once again)

1502
01:01:16,229 --> 01:01:18,998
Forget about being courageous. I won't be courageous.

1503
01:01:18,999 --> 01:01:22,168
Should we shoot a video message for Mr. CO KUN?

1504
01:01:22,169 --> 01:01:23,169
(His last hope was Mr. CO KUN.)

1505
01:01:23,539 --> 01:01:24,638
(Mr. CO KUN!)

1506
01:01:24,639 --> 01:01:25,939
(When is he coming?)

1507
01:01:27,609 --> 01:01:29,739
Hey, why...

1508
01:01:30,409 --> 01:01:31,778
What's wrong with you?

1509
01:01:31,779 --> 01:01:34,148
Because they should see him.

1510
01:01:34,149 --> 01:01:36,748
Should we really try giving Mr. CO KUN a call?

1511
01:01:36,749 --> 01:01:38,388
Should we really call him?

1512
01:01:38,389 --> 01:01:39,448
- Really?
- Yes.

1513
01:01:39,449 --> 01:01:40,988
Okay. Let's call him.

1514
01:01:40,989 --> 01:01:42,418
- Really, Mr. CO KUN.
- Really?

1515
01:01:42,419 --> 01:01:43,919
- Mr. CO KUN?
- We'll call him.

1516
01:01:45,159 --> 01:01:46,359
Hello?

1517
01:01:46,729 --> 01:01:47,899
Mr. CO KUN.

1518
01:01:48,559 --> 01:01:49,559
Yes?

1519
01:01:49,560 --> 01:01:50,728
The kids...

1520
01:01:50,729 --> 01:01:53,329
Let me. Hey, CO KUN.

1521
01:01:53,369 --> 01:01:55,968
- The kids are crying.
- Why?

1522
01:01:55,969 --> 01:01:57,609
Tell them to stop crying.

1523
01:01:57,939 --> 01:02:00,668
Tell them to stop crying and that you'll come to see them.

1524
01:02:00,669 --> 01:02:01,979
Please tell them to stop.

1525
01:02:02,379 --> 01:02:05,148
- Okay.
- Here's Mr. CO KUN's voice.

1526
01:02:05,149 --> 01:02:07,779
Mr. CO KUN, please speak.

1527
01:02:08,286 --> 01:02:09,716
The kids are crying.

1528
01:02:10,186 --> 01:02:12,386
- Why?
- Tell them to stop crying.

1529
01:02:12,816 --> 01:02:14,186
Tell them to stop crying...

1530
01:02:14,386 --> 01:02:16,686
and that you'll come to see them. Please tell them to stop.

1531
01:02:17,286 --> 01:02:19,856
- Okay.
- Here's Mr. CO KUN's voice.

1532
01:02:20,026 --> 01:02:22,496
Mr. CO KUN, please speak.

1533
01:02:22,896 --> 01:02:23,966
Hey, everyone.

1534
01:02:24,236 --> 01:02:25,236
(Wailing)

1535
01:02:25,466 --> 01:02:26,835
Hey, let's hang up.

1536
01:02:26,836 --> 01:02:27,836
(Hurriedly)

1537
01:02:28,236 --> 01:02:30,105
Hey, cut this out.

1538
01:02:30,106 --> 01:02:31,535
(Even Mr. CO KUN, whom they trusted, has failed.)

1539
01:02:31,536 --> 01:02:32,805
Hang up. It won't work.

1540
01:02:32,806 --> 01:02:35,206
- I'm sad about something.
- Why? What is it?

1541
01:02:35,406 --> 01:02:37,476
- You're all crying like this.
- Yes.

1542
01:02:37,576 --> 01:02:38,915
Why...

1543
01:02:38,916 --> 01:02:43,016
didn't you express your feelings more actively before?

1544
01:02:44,086 --> 01:02:45,715
Because I couldn't keep up physically.

1545
01:02:45,716 --> 01:02:47,726
- What? Is that so?
- My body didn't follow my emotions.

1546
01:02:48,256 --> 01:02:49,426
Mr. Choi.

1547
01:02:49,856 --> 01:02:52,226
Potato Teacher, I love you.

1548
01:02:52,956 --> 01:02:54,466
I love you.

1549
01:02:56,896 --> 01:02:59,836
- Ms. Kim, I love you.
- I love you.

1550
01:03:02,666 --> 01:03:03,835
North Pole Teacher.

1551
01:03:03,836 --> 01:03:05,935
(Confessing their love at the top of their lungs)

1552
01:03:05,936 --> 01:03:08,106
North Pole Teacher, I love you.

1553
01:03:10,676 --> 01:03:13,816
I love you too.

1554
01:03:15,286 --> 01:03:20,316
(The true feelings of the children they didn't know about)

1555
01:03:22,156 --> 01:03:25,226
Please give me a hug.

1556
01:03:27,796 --> 01:03:29,496
Who'll be the first to hug me?

1557
01:03:30,196 --> 01:03:31,866
Who'll come to me first?

1558
01:03:32,336 --> 01:03:36,006
- Who'll come to me?
- Go.

1559
01:03:36,066 --> 01:03:37,405
Come here.

1560
01:03:37,406 --> 01:03:39,176
(The hugging class)

1561
01:03:40,206 --> 01:03:42,806
(Me too.)

1562
01:03:43,546 --> 01:03:45,376
- Can't you stay?
- What?

1563
01:03:45,446 --> 01:03:47,246
Can't you stay?

1564
01:03:47,846 --> 01:03:51,015
I'm not going anywhere yet, Eun Soo.

1565
01:03:51,016 --> 01:03:54,325
We have more time, Eun Soo.

1566
01:03:54,326 --> 01:03:55,686
- Are you leaving?
- What?

1567
01:03:55,786 --> 01:03:57,185
Do you want to say something?

1568
01:03:57,186 --> 01:03:58,726
Please calm them down.

1569
01:03:58,896 --> 01:04:00,456
I'll calm them down.

1570
01:04:00,696 --> 01:04:02,026
No.

1571
01:04:02,196 --> 01:04:03,426
Are you all right?

1572
01:04:04,836 --> 01:04:05,996
- Are you okay?
- Yes.

1573
01:04:07,296 --> 01:04:09,366
This isn't our last time.

1574
01:04:10,506 --> 01:04:12,206
Aren't you going to be the one who'll leave me?

1575
01:04:12,636 --> 01:04:14,646
Are you going to abandon me when the puberty hits you?

1576
01:04:15,946 --> 01:04:16,976
No?

1577
01:04:17,176 --> 01:04:18,675
- Let's keep in touch. Okay?
- Yes.

1578
01:04:18,676 --> 01:04:20,915
- Even if we can't meet up often.
- Okay.

1579
01:04:20,916 --> 01:04:23,686
(Ha Yun, who has always been calm, sheds tears.)

1580
01:04:25,486 --> 01:04:27,656
They've approached the play...

1581
01:04:28,286 --> 01:04:30,356
more sincerely than I thought.

1582
01:04:31,126 --> 01:04:32,355
They love theater.

1583
01:04:32,356 --> 01:04:35,796
They love being with us.

1584
01:04:37,026 --> 01:04:38,596
I do feel the same.

1585
01:04:39,896 --> 01:04:43,306
"Are the children feeling the same, though?"

1586
01:04:43,606 --> 01:04:47,136
I had my doubts.

1587
01:04:49,676 --> 01:04:52,446
But I was totally wrong. Yes.

1588
01:04:55,486 --> 01:04:57,755
I didn't expect the kids to cry like that.

1589
01:04:57,756 --> 01:04:59,955
(Their true feelings touched one another today.)

1590
01:04:59,956 --> 01:05:01,655
I was shocked.

1591
01:05:01,656 --> 01:05:03,326
It was the first time in my life.

1592
01:05:04,019 --> 01:05:08,359
(After the camp full of tears is over)

1593
01:05:08,959 --> 01:05:10,859
Do Hyun told me, "I love you."

1594
01:05:12,489 --> 01:05:14,459
- He said that to all three of us.
- "I love you."

1595
01:05:14,659 --> 01:05:15,699
Yes.

1596
01:05:17,399 --> 01:05:19,569
It was so heartfelt.

1597
01:05:19,699 --> 01:05:21,169
- "I love you." - "I love you."

1598
01:05:23,569 --> 01:05:25,038
It's not easy for us...

1599
01:05:25,039 --> 01:05:26,809
- to say, "I love you." - Exactly.

1600
01:05:27,209 --> 01:05:29,879
Even my wife doesn't say she loves me these days.

1601
01:05:31,609 --> 01:05:33,509
- But they went, "I love you!" - Thank you.

1602
01:05:33,679 --> 01:05:35,078
They look tasty.

1603
01:05:35,079 --> 01:05:36,579
(Maybe the grownups are clumsier when expressing their feelings.)

1604
01:05:37,619 --> 01:05:38,788
I was so shocked.

1605
01:05:38,789 --> 01:05:40,848
(The feelings linger.)

1606
01:05:40,849 --> 01:05:42,789
I heard they cried all the way home.

1607
01:05:44,429 --> 01:05:47,899
I'm shy to say, "I love you."

1608
01:05:49,199 --> 01:05:52,698
But once the children feels love in their hearts,

1609
01:05:52,699 --> 01:05:54,739
they speak it out loud without a problem.

1610
01:05:54,839 --> 01:05:56,769
- We should learn from them.
- North Pole Teacher, I love you.

1611
01:05:58,409 --> 01:06:00,208
Children are much better at that.

1612
01:06:00,209 --> 01:06:02,508
(The children taught him how to express his feelings.)

1613
01:06:02,509 --> 01:06:03,609
They cried.

1614
01:06:04,349 --> 01:06:07,079
I've never seen people crying like that in my life.

1615
01:06:07,619 --> 01:06:09,178
I should learn about them.

1616
01:06:09,179 --> 01:06:10,579
I feel like I don't know a thing.

1617
01:06:12,519 --> 01:06:15,859
They showed us how they really felt. It was...

1618
01:06:19,859 --> 01:06:22,528
It was really shocking.

1619
01:06:22,529 --> 01:06:24,268
(They realized they felt the same that night.)

1620
01:06:24,269 --> 01:06:25,798
- Did you watch it?
- No.

1621
01:06:25,799 --> 01:06:27,969
- Should we watch it?
- What is that?

1622
01:06:28,499 --> 01:06:30,638
Hyo Min shot it with this camera.

1623
01:06:30,639 --> 01:06:31,968
He interviewed us.

1624
01:06:31,969 --> 01:06:33,509
(While the North Pole Teacher was preparing for the camp,)

1625
01:06:36,179 --> 01:06:37,478
He shot a lot.

1626
01:06:37,479 --> 01:06:39,678
(the kids shot a video.)

1627
01:06:39,679 --> 01:06:41,478
Okay. Well.

1628
01:06:41,479 --> 01:06:44,219
How did you feel while working with us?

1629
01:06:44,649 --> 01:06:45,819
- That's a good question.
- Goodness.

1630
01:06:46,189 --> 01:06:47,589
It's a legit interview.

1631
01:06:47,789 --> 01:06:48,959
Let me do this once.

1632
01:06:49,059 --> 01:06:50,458
You don't have it.

1633
01:06:50,459 --> 01:06:52,959
Let's take a vlog from now on.

1634
01:06:53,089 --> 01:06:54,089
Okay.

1635
01:06:54,090 --> 01:06:55,559
It's for the memories.

1636
01:06:56,429 --> 01:06:58,568
We'll begin our class vlog.

1637
01:06:58,569 --> 01:07:00,299
(The teachers shot by the students after the class)

1638
01:07:01,039 --> 01:07:02,998
- Hello.
- Hello.

1639
01:07:02,999 --> 01:07:04,508
- Hello.
- Okay. Today...

1640
01:07:04,509 --> 01:07:05,638
- Who are you?
- Please introduce yourself.

1641
01:07:05,639 --> 01:07:07,778
- Who are you?
- We're going to do an interview.

1642
01:07:07,779 --> 01:07:08,779
- Who are you?
- Yes.

1643
01:07:08,780 --> 01:07:10,179
Did you have trouble sleeping?

1644
01:07:11,009 --> 01:07:12,609
(Yawning)

1645
01:07:12,879 --> 01:07:14,679
- No.
- Why aren't you being responsive?

1646
01:07:15,279 --> 01:07:16,418
- I slept well.
- Why?

1647
01:07:16,419 --> 01:07:17,988
We need to see some reactions.

1648
01:07:17,989 --> 01:07:19,348
- Do you want reactions?
- Or...

1649
01:07:19,349 --> 01:07:20,589
I love it. I'm happy.

1650
01:07:20,949 --> 01:07:22,958
Okay. That's too short.

1651
01:07:22,959 --> 01:07:24,158
- Please tell us more.
- That's right.

1652
01:07:24,159 --> 01:07:26,789
It seems as if you don't love us.

1653
01:07:27,999 --> 01:07:29,828
(Scolded)

1654
01:07:29,829 --> 01:07:32,168
- Ms. Kim is doing great.
- I...

1655
01:07:32,169 --> 01:07:34,338
- We need your unconditional love.
- Do I get a pass?

1656
01:07:34,339 --> 01:07:35,768
- But Potato Teacher is...
- Yes, Ms. Kim.

1657
01:07:35,769 --> 01:07:36,968
- Do I get a pass?
- You passed.

1658
01:07:36,969 --> 01:07:38,968
- But Ha Yun.
- Yes?

1659
01:07:38,969 --> 01:07:40,939
You know how much I show my love every day, right?

1660
01:07:41,239 --> 01:07:43,039
Tell them about my true feelings.

1661
01:07:43,579 --> 01:07:45,548
- How Potato Teacher is...
- As for Potato Teacher,

1662
01:07:45,549 --> 01:07:47,878
he really cares for us.

1663
01:07:47,879 --> 01:07:49,748
He just can't say it because he's shy.

1664
01:07:49,749 --> 01:07:51,349
It's okay. Just tell us.

1665
01:07:51,489 --> 01:07:52,718
- I have a question.
- Okay.

1666
01:07:52,719 --> 01:07:56,288
We're going to say goodbye soon.

1667
01:07:56,289 --> 01:07:58,189
- That's sad.
- What will happen?

1668
01:07:59,059 --> 01:08:00,588
- I think I'll cry.
- What...

1669
01:08:00,589 --> 01:08:01,898
I think I'll cry.

1670
01:08:01,899 --> 01:08:03,259
- Really?
- Yes.

1671
01:08:04,199 --> 01:08:06,198
I think tears will stream down.

1672
01:08:06,199 --> 01:08:08,769
- I'll cry.
- I'll cry my eyes out.

1673
01:08:09,769 --> 01:08:10,968
It's going to be sad.

1674
01:08:10,969 --> 01:08:12,509
Here's how I feel, everyone.

1675
01:08:13,609 --> 01:08:16,008
When the play is over...

1676
01:08:16,009 --> 01:08:18,178
We practiced together...

1677
01:08:18,179 --> 01:08:19,879
and performed a play together.

1678
01:08:20,049 --> 01:08:23,249
When you go on about your life and become grownups,

1679
01:08:23,449 --> 01:08:26,949
I hope you'll think of this moment at some point in your life...

1680
01:08:27,149 --> 01:08:29,289
in whatever way it may be.

1681
01:08:33,389 --> 01:08:37,259
Hello. It's time for a solo interview.

1682
01:08:38,429 --> 01:08:40,028
(Every question is embraced with love.)

1683
01:08:40,029 --> 01:08:41,698
- Should we do a proper one?
- We're shooting it right now.

1684
01:08:41,699 --> 01:08:43,499
- Do you want a proper interview?
- Yes.

1685
01:08:44,639 --> 01:08:46,139
- Ask me the question.
- Okay.

1686
01:08:46,239 --> 01:08:49,308
How was it to teach us in the acting class,

1687
01:08:49,309 --> 01:08:51,678
and how do you feel?

1688
01:08:51,679 --> 01:08:53,908
For me, every day...

1689
01:08:53,909 --> 01:08:55,948
(For me, every day...)

1690
01:08:55,949 --> 01:08:57,449
was a rollercoaster ride.

1691
01:08:58,849 --> 01:09:00,488
I've been doing my best.

1692
01:09:00,489 --> 01:09:04,189
I don't know if the students know that.

1693
01:09:04,629 --> 01:09:09,199
Now, do you feel like time with us is short?

1694
01:09:09,329 --> 01:09:13,728
I feel like it's way too short.

1695
01:09:13,729 --> 01:09:15,338
In that case,

1696
01:09:15,339 --> 01:09:19,539
I recommend that you make this a regular class.

1697
01:09:20,769 --> 01:09:22,778
Hyo Min, are you going to take the acting class if there's one?

1698
01:09:22,779 --> 01:09:23,809
Yes.

1699
01:09:24,339 --> 01:09:25,509
- Are you going to take it again?
- Yes.

1700
01:09:25,879 --> 01:09:26,978
- Is it fun?
- Yes.

1701
01:09:26,979 --> 01:09:28,178
- That's right.
- That's great.

1702
01:09:28,179 --> 01:09:29,249
What?

1703
01:09:29,349 --> 01:09:30,378
Of course.

1704
01:09:30,379 --> 01:09:31,418
- In that case, - I need to hear you.

1705
01:09:31,419 --> 01:09:33,448
- this is the last question.
- Okay.

1706
01:09:33,449 --> 01:09:35,058
- Here's the last question.
- Okay.

1707
01:09:35,059 --> 01:09:36,359
Do you like us?

1708
01:09:37,289 --> 01:09:38,388
I love you guys so much.

1709
01:09:38,389 --> 01:09:43,399
(I love you guys so much.)

1710
01:09:47,799 --> 01:09:51,308
(Their hearts are full of love like the full moon.)

1711
01:09:51,309 --> 01:09:52,309
What? The fireworks?

1712
01:09:52,310 --> 01:09:54,439
- Let's go and do fireworks.
- Yes. Sounds good.

1713
01:09:54,639 --> 01:09:56,109
It'll be crazy.

1714
01:09:59,079 --> 01:10:01,048
(The place where they received the fierce confession)

1715
01:10:01,049 --> 01:10:02,119
Here.

1716
01:10:06,449 --> 01:10:08,789
(They light up the firework, instead of their hearts.)

1717
01:10:09,019 --> 01:10:10,419
It's pretty.

1718
01:10:16,629 --> 01:10:19,399
(Filmed by Tae Ri)

1719
01:10:20,629 --> 01:10:21,799
This is so interesting.

1720
01:10:25,369 --> 01:10:28,609
(The star instructor is back.)

1721
01:10:32,109 --> 01:10:33,378
(Due to the aftermath of the confession,)

1722
01:10:33,379 --> 01:10:36,049
(the night at the Mushroom House won't settle down.)

1723
01:10:37,649 --> 01:10:38,649
Do it excitedly.

1724
01:10:38,650 --> 01:10:40,748
It clears my mind so bright

1725
01:10:40,749 --> 01:10:44,888
Today, I was able to sort out some thoughts.

1726
01:10:44,889 --> 01:10:45,929
Nice!

1727
01:10:46,159 --> 01:10:48,098
I should try my best.

1728
01:10:48,099 --> 01:10:49,629
(The true feelings touched everyone's heart today.)

1729
01:10:50,059 --> 01:10:51,329
It was as good...

1730
01:10:52,069 --> 01:10:53,169
as it could be.

1731
01:10:56,569 --> 01:10:59,869
(The acting class is heading toward the end.)

1732
01:11:02,079 --> 01:11:05,849
(They're getting their acts together one more time.)

1733
01:11:08,679 --> 01:11:10,648
(The school arts festival is approaching.)

1734
01:11:10,649 --> 01:11:11,689
Ta-da!

1735
01:11:11,789 --> 01:11:13,449
(The costumes for the play have arrived.)

1736
01:11:13,919 --> 01:11:17,089
(They transform into their characters.)

1737
01:11:17,489 --> 01:11:19,429
(Mr. CO's music helps them focus completely.)

1738
01:11:20,229 --> 01:11:23,329
(Their acting skills have improved.)

1739
01:11:24,229 --> 01:11:25,869
(The play has become richer now.)

1740
01:11:26,329 --> 01:11:28,439
(To understand how the students really feel,)

1741
01:11:28,969 --> 01:11:30,939
(there will be 1-on-1 after-school dates.)

1742
01:11:31,409 --> 01:11:33,409
(Expressing their feelings with sincerity)

1743
01:11:34,109 --> 01:11:35,379
(I can do it.)

1744
01:11:35,839 --> 01:11:38,079
(Say it louder.)

1745
01:11:38,379 --> 01:11:40,649
(Instilling confidence)

1746
01:11:41,349 --> 01:11:43,279
(And taking them back home without a problem)

1747
01:11:43,919 --> 01:11:45,849
(And the guest they're happy to see)

1748
01:11:46,589 --> 01:11:49,889
(Barista KUN is back.)

1749
01:11:50,889 --> 01:11:54,089
(The whole gang checks out the stage for the first time.)

1750
01:11:54,599 --> 01:11:57,359
(They're flustered as it's bigger than they thought.)

1751
01:11:57,829 --> 01:11:59,868
(Unexpected variables keep on coming.)

1752
01:11:59,869 --> 01:12:01,369
(Flapping)

1753
01:12:03,599 --> 01:12:06,039
(My mind went blank again at that moment.)

1754
01:12:06,569 --> 01:12:10,179
(Will they be able to finish the rehearsal without a problem?)

1755
01:12:12,379 --> 01:12:14,878
(The OST of Curtain Up, Class!)

1756
01:12:14,879 --> 01:12:17,318
("Let's Just Go!" by Seok Matthew, Kim Tae Rae,)

1757
01:12:17,319 --> 01:12:19,788
(and Park Gun Wook of ZEROBASEONE)

1758
01:12:19,789 --> 01:12:22,189
(Available on all music streaming sites)

1759
01:12:49,760 --> 01:12:51,760
Dramaday.me
